1
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:32,783
The most entertaining suspense
that predicts love.

2
00:00:32,783 --> 00:00:34,833
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

3
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:39,033
Five people with sharp romance
radars have gathered.

4
00:00:39,033 --> 00:00:41,783
[The panel of five people is here]

5
00:00:41,783 --> 00:00:47,073
Last week, they played the truth game,
which made everyone nervous.

6
00:00:47,073 --> 00:00:50,983
- I couldn't breathe.
- I'm traumatized by the truth game now.

7
00:00:50,983 --> 00:00:54,603
The highlight of it was Gyu Ri and Wu Yeol.

8
00:00:54,603 --> 00:00:56,823
It was like they were
only playing with each other.

9
00:00:56,823 --> 00:00:59,793
I've never felt this way on Heart Signal.

10
00:00:59,793 --> 00:01:02,183
Tell me the lines that you find memorable.

11
00:01:02,183 --> 00:01:04,353
"You're curious about me?"

12
00:01:04,353 --> 00:01:06,033
You're curious about me?

13
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:07,763
And there was Seo Won's comment.

14
00:01:07,763 --> 00:01:09,933
Is 70-80% insignificant?

15
00:01:11,183 --> 00:01:12,953
That was so...

16
00:01:12,953 --> 00:01:16,393
He was basically saying, "Enough is enough."

17
00:01:16,393 --> 00:01:17,683
Right.

18
00:01:17,683 --> 00:01:20,843
Seo Won was like, "That's enough.

19
00:01:20,843 --> 00:01:22,693
Is 70-80% insignificant?

20
00:01:22,693 --> 00:01:26,173
Is it insignificant? What am I, then?

21
00:01:26,173 --> 00:01:28,473
What if I said you were 70-80% to me?"

22
00:01:28,473 --> 00:01:31,293
- That's enough.
- I'm just glad...

23
00:01:31,293 --> 00:01:33,553
that Sang Min was a singer.

24
00:01:33,553 --> 00:01:35,663
Good thing you didn't act.

25
00:01:35,663 --> 00:01:38,903
What would you have said
if you were asked that?

26
00:01:38,903 --> 00:01:41,823
I would've been like,
"My percentage is that high?"

27
00:01:41,823 --> 00:01:44,123
[LOL]

28
00:01:44,123 --> 00:01:46,343
[Wow, thank you!]

29
00:01:46,343 --> 00:01:50,873
Beluga of the Forest asked
My Dog, Yellow, out on a date.

30
00:01:50,873 --> 00:01:57,953
She gave him a Valentine's Day gift, saying,
"This reminded me of you."

31
00:01:57,953 --> 00:02:01,433
- That was clever.
- Didn't they have similar hobbies, too?

32
00:02:01,433 --> 00:02:02,853
They're both into musicals, too.

33
00:02:02,853 --> 00:02:08,223
That got me wondering if Yu Gyeong
was interested in Jun Hyeon.

34
00:02:08,223 --> 00:02:11,423
But we saw her giving Wu Yeol a straw shoe.

35
00:02:11,423 --> 00:02:13,983
- Anyway, Wu Yeol has a presence.
- So strong.

36
00:02:13,983 --> 00:02:15,733
- Right in front of her.
- So, it's not easy.

37
00:02:15,733 --> 00:02:17,113
The straw shoe was huge.

38
00:02:17,113 --> 00:02:19,733
And the four of them went to a bowling alley.

39
00:02:19,733 --> 00:02:20,823
From what we saw,

40
00:02:20,823 --> 00:02:23,633
So Yun's feelings for Seo Won became clear.

41
00:02:23,633 --> 00:02:25,143
She was so charming.

42
00:02:25,143 --> 00:02:27,703
She tried to steal a high five, too.

43
00:02:27,703 --> 00:02:30,943
The aggressive side of So Yun that we knew of

44
00:02:30,943 --> 00:02:32,853
was shown at the bowling alley again.
It was nice.

45
00:02:32,853 --> 00:02:35,483
Right, I thought she was a bowling ball.

46
00:02:35,483 --> 00:02:36,793
[Strike!]

47
00:02:36,793 --> 00:02:40,083
She has a very proactive style.

48
00:02:40,083 --> 00:02:42,863
Life in Signal House
is already close to an end.

49
00:02:42,863 --> 00:02:46,393
Let's see what events are awaiting them.

50
00:02:46,393 --> 00:02:48,873
[After the truth game]

51
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:53,223
Yes, we have to do our best.

52
00:02:53,223 --> 00:02:56,293
So, we are left with no regrets.

53
00:02:58,363 --> 00:03:01,593
That's not how I felt.

54
00:03:01,593 --> 00:03:04,443
This situation is just...

55
00:03:05,393 --> 00:03:07,403
I'll try to understand.

56
00:03:07,403 --> 00:03:09,773
What do we do?

57
00:03:16,643 --> 00:03:18,463
But I...

58
00:03:19,563 --> 00:03:22,143
I've shared my feelings before.

59
00:03:23,823 --> 00:03:25,683
I'm glad I got two.

60
00:03:25,683 --> 00:03:27,273
What? What do we do?

61
00:03:27,273 --> 00:03:30,353
[People are gathering in the living room]

62
00:03:30,353 --> 00:03:32,553
Gosh.

63
00:03:32,553 --> 00:03:35,233
Are they different flavors?

64
00:03:35,233 --> 00:03:40,273
[Their conversation was interrupted]

65
00:03:51,713 --> 00:03:55,033
[Wu Yeol was not able to finish his sentence]

66
00:03:55,033 --> 00:03:56,873
What cruel timing.

67
00:04:07,593 --> 00:04:11,833
[Yu Gyeong is leaving the room]

68
00:04:26,853 --> 00:04:29,533
Do you want water? Should I get you some?

69
00:04:30,503 --> 00:04:32,763
Things are complicated.

70
00:04:34,123 --> 00:04:37,153
[Wu Yeol is going to the second floor]

71
00:04:42,043 --> 00:04:44,083
[Lurking around the door]

72
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:46,583
[Waiting for Yu Gyeong]

73
00:04:46,583 --> 00:04:49,253
Is he waiting for her to come out?

74
00:05:00,683 --> 00:05:03,803
Right, a few days ago...

75
00:05:08,163 --> 00:05:09,673
Never mind.

76
00:05:11,113 --> 00:05:13,673
It's too embarrassing to talk about.

77
00:05:13,673 --> 00:05:14,873
Why?

78
00:05:19,123 --> 00:05:21,633
- You're having fun on your own.
- What?

79
00:05:21,633 --> 00:05:24,333
How can you have so much fun alone?
I want to know, too.

80
00:05:26,283 --> 00:05:28,993
- What?
- It's nothing.

81
00:05:30,953 --> 00:05:32,933
Tell me.

82
00:05:39,383 --> 00:05:42,673
Well, you were in my dream.

83
00:05:50,313 --> 00:05:51,903
What did we do?

84
00:05:53,213 --> 00:05:57,483
[Just thinking about it makes her laugh]

85
00:05:57,483 --> 00:05:59,723
Guess what we did?

86
00:06:01,383 --> 00:06:04,043
You won't be able to guess.

87
00:06:04,043 --> 00:06:05,893
Did we have a fist fight?

88
00:06:05,893 --> 00:06:07,993
We didn't!

89
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:12,473
- We did a triathlon.
- Huh?

90
00:06:12,473 --> 00:06:14,243
What kind of dream is that?

91
00:06:14,243 --> 00:06:17,593
We swam across the Han River.

92
00:06:17,593 --> 00:06:19,813
- And we biked, too?
- Yes.

93
00:06:23,413 --> 00:06:25,343
Didn't I look so sleepy yesterday?

94
00:06:25,343 --> 00:06:27,903
Yes, I felt sorry for you.

95
00:06:27,903 --> 00:06:29,753
You were like...

96
00:06:31,013 --> 00:06:32,553
I felt bad for you.

97
00:06:32,553 --> 00:06:35,433
I was incredibly tired yesterday.

98
00:06:36,303 --> 00:06:37,613
[Forcing eyes open]

99
00:06:37,613 --> 00:06:39,383
Your eyelids doubled.

100
00:06:39,383 --> 00:06:41,783
And then I was like...

101
00:06:41,783 --> 00:06:43,433
I kept acting like that.

102
00:06:43,433 --> 00:06:47,843
I know. That's why
I didn't get to hear you talk.

103
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:58,483
I'm curious how you resolve conflicts.

104
00:06:58,483 --> 00:06:59,843
Me?

105
00:07:02,183 --> 00:07:04,983
- Gosh.
- Yu Gyeong is so out of it.

106
00:07:11,453 --> 00:07:12,683
Me?

107
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:15,853
I don't raise my voice that much.

108
00:07:16,813 --> 00:07:18,543
You talk quietly?

109
00:07:18,543 --> 00:07:20,643
I don't try to win.

110
00:07:20,643 --> 00:07:23,963
I used to try to because I felt wronged.

111
00:07:23,963 --> 00:07:25,903
I feel wronged.

112
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:30,403
But I realized at some point that
winning doesn't get you anything.

113
00:07:30,403 --> 00:07:35,093
I'd try if somebody gave me a badge of honor.

114
00:07:36,433 --> 00:07:40,233
But winning isn't necessarily good.

115
00:07:41,163 --> 00:07:42,833
I don't try to win.

116
00:07:43,693 --> 00:07:45,653
But you have to experience that.

117
00:07:45,653 --> 00:07:50,673
I raised my voice when I was upset,
trying to win.

118
00:07:50,673 --> 00:07:53,843
But at some point, I was like,
"What am I doing?"

119
00:07:53,843 --> 00:07:55,483
Why should I...

120
00:07:57,413 --> 00:08:00,183
- What's the point in trying to win?
- He's right.

121
00:08:00,183 --> 00:08:02,483
I just say everything is okay.

122
00:08:02,483 --> 00:08:04,093
Really?

123
00:08:04,093 --> 00:08:08,853
To be honest, fighting and
raising your voice at each other

124
00:08:08,853 --> 00:08:13,793
and getting angry scares me.

125
00:08:15,633 --> 00:08:21,733
But I think I'm like that...

126
00:08:26,673 --> 00:08:29,673
Looks like you require time, too.

127
00:08:29,673 --> 00:08:30,933
To calm down?

128
00:08:30,933 --> 00:08:32,683
- No.
- No? Do you calm down right away?

129
00:08:32,683 --> 00:08:35,333
Yes. I can't take time.

130
00:08:36,183 --> 00:08:39,683
I try to avoid. Otherwise, I'll die.

131
00:08:40,673 --> 00:08:44,533
I really can't do it. It's too hard for me.

132
00:08:44,533 --> 00:08:47,673
I prefer to resolve things right away, too.

133
00:08:47,673 --> 00:08:50,763
I used to be frustrated and couldn't
understand the avoidant type.

134
00:08:50,763 --> 00:08:53,023
But I understand them now.

135
00:08:53,023 --> 00:08:56,343
- You try to understand?
- Because they...

136
00:08:57,023 --> 00:08:59,983
- need to adjust things themselves.
- They need time.

137
00:08:59,983 --> 00:09:02,483
I used to find it very frustrating.

138
00:09:04,853 --> 00:09:07,083
But you have to understand.

139
00:09:07,083 --> 00:09:09,793
You need to think from the
other person's perspective.

140
00:09:14,883 --> 00:09:16,423
Really?

141
00:09:16,423 --> 00:09:18,263
You think I'm lying?

142
00:09:19,773 --> 00:09:22,123
Think from the other person's perspective.

143
00:09:22,123 --> 00:09:26,063
Right. Understanding resolves everything.

144
00:09:26,063 --> 00:09:28,293
There's no reason not to.

145
00:09:37,893 --> 00:09:40,703
It's so hard in so many ways.

146
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:00,893
[Getting up]

147
00:10:17,603 --> 00:10:19,503
She's standing in front of Wu Yeol.

148
00:10:24,703 --> 00:10:26,413
He doesn't care.

149
00:10:28,273 --> 00:10:31,323
[Yu Gyeong is coming down to the first floor]

150
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:36,873
[Glancing]

151
00:10:36,873 --> 00:10:40,333
She keeps looking for her chance.

152
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:41,913
She's here.

153
00:10:54,243 --> 00:10:56,603
[Drinking cold water]

154
00:11:00,863 --> 00:11:03,463
You know the things you told Yu Gyeong?

155
00:11:03,463 --> 00:11:05,943
What do you think about that?

156
00:11:07,643 --> 00:11:10,353
I've only been considering
Yu Gyeong all this time.

157
00:11:10,353 --> 00:11:12,343
So Yun, can I have this?

158
00:11:12,343 --> 00:11:14,193
She's back.

159
00:11:15,033 --> 00:11:16,693
Why are you avoiding me?

160
00:11:16,693 --> 00:11:19,523
- Why are you avoiding me while I'm talking?
- No, I was thinking.

161
00:11:19,523 --> 00:11:21,443
I was thinking while listening to you.

162
00:11:21,443 --> 00:11:25,253
[Yu Gyeong is back to the same spot]

163
00:11:25,253 --> 00:11:26,993
She's sitting next to him.

164
00:11:32,073 --> 00:11:33,333
[Glancing]

165
00:11:37,873 --> 00:11:39,633
Did you feel frustrated?

166
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:44,533
I've been wanting to talk to you.

167
00:11:44,533 --> 00:11:46,333
Darn.

168
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:49,933
[Throw a cup of water at him (?)]

169
00:11:51,243 --> 00:11:55,743
[Can he tell her now what he couldn't say?]

170
00:11:55,743 --> 00:11:58,313
Yu Gyeong is mature.

171
00:11:58,313 --> 00:12:00,173
She's so nice.

172
00:12:00,843 --> 00:12:02,933
This is crazy. We got something.

173
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:04,873
- We got a text.
- Really?

174
00:12:04,873 --> 00:12:06,363
- Really?
- About dates?

175
00:12:06,363 --> 00:12:09,177
[There will be third official dates. Ask
someone out between 12 and 1 tomorrow.]

176
00:12:09,177 --> 00:12:11,567
My head hurts. My head hurts.

177
00:12:12,853 --> 00:12:14,563
Ask someone out directly?

178
00:12:14,563 --> 00:12:17,613
They have to ask someone out
directly instead of texting?

179
00:12:17,613 --> 00:12:20,073
They can go on a date
with anyone they choose.

180
00:12:20,073 --> 00:12:23,253
Okay. So, everyone can.

181
00:12:23,253 --> 00:12:24,303
Wow.

182
00:12:24,303 --> 00:12:26,633
They have to ask someone out like this?

183
00:12:26,633 --> 00:12:29,133
[There is a lot to think about this evening]

184
00:12:31,983 --> 00:12:34,463
[The morning after]

185
00:12:35,193 --> 00:12:37,693
Min Ju wants to transform today.

186
00:12:37,693 --> 00:12:38,813
It's about time.

187
00:12:38,813 --> 00:12:42,333
[Everyone is starting the day busily]

188
00:12:51,003 --> 00:12:53,953
I'm asking you out on a date.

189
00:12:54,933 --> 00:12:58,513
She keeps practicing
how she's going to bring it up.

190
00:12:58,513 --> 00:13:01,403
Fighting. You look pretty today.

191
00:13:03,933 --> 00:13:06,433
Oh! Is he here to ask someone out?

192
00:13:09,513 --> 00:13:12,223
- Min Ju is right there.
- Oh, no.

193
00:13:12,223 --> 00:13:14,893
Yu Gyeong? You want me to get her?

194
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:16,933
Please.

195
00:13:16,933 --> 00:13:21,333
Yu Gyeong, Seong Min wants me to get you.

196
00:13:23,523 --> 00:13:25,153
Just one second.

197
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:28,803
- It's pissing her off!
- Seriously!

198
00:13:28,803 --> 00:13:30,423
Gosh.

199
00:13:31,183 --> 00:13:33,323
What do we do?

200
00:13:33,323 --> 00:13:34,953
It's time to ask someone out.

201
00:13:34,953 --> 00:13:37,893
Yu Gyeong must feel so uncomfortable.

202
00:13:42,943 --> 00:13:44,843
Do you want to go on a date?

203
00:13:45,543 --> 00:13:49,013
Yes. Okay, let's.

204
00:13:50,063 --> 00:13:51,703
Thank you.

205
00:13:52,413 --> 00:13:54,383
You were reading a book.

206
00:13:58,123 --> 00:13:59,543
[Worried]

207
00:14:04,743 --> 00:14:06,193
Gosh, this is crazy.

208
00:14:06,193 --> 00:14:08,753
- Min Ju can't believe it.
- Of course, she can't.

209
00:14:08,753 --> 00:14:11,113
That's the right reaction.

210
00:14:11,113 --> 00:14:12,373
Of all people.

211
00:14:12,373 --> 00:14:14,143
Wow, seriously.

212
00:14:14,803 --> 00:14:17,603
But I'm not upset.

213
00:14:18,343 --> 00:14:20,373
I guess I've been upset all this time.

214
00:14:20,373 --> 00:14:24,173
- She's been upset.
- It's because she has low expectations.

215
00:14:26,773 --> 00:14:31,393
[Seo Won is getting ready for his date, too]

216
00:14:36,083 --> 00:14:37,503
[Moist]

217
00:14:41,893 --> 00:14:44,043
- So Yun needs to make a move.
- Go, So Yun!

218
00:14:44,043 --> 00:14:46,283
- I can't do it.
- Why? You just need to do it.

219
00:14:46,283 --> 00:14:47,593
I can't do it.

220
00:14:47,593 --> 00:14:49,953
You can't think of what to say?

221
00:14:51,313 --> 00:14:53,713
I'll just be natural.

222
00:14:55,123 --> 00:14:56,983
Let's go.

223
00:15:05,453 --> 00:15:06,673
Did you sleep well?

224
00:15:06,673 --> 00:15:07,893
Yes.

225
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:14,483
- You look cool today.
- Thanks.

226
00:15:14,483 --> 00:15:17,773
Do you have time today or tomorrow?

227
00:15:17,773 --> 00:15:18,733
I'm free today.
- Huh?
- I'm free today.

228
00:15:19,733 --> 00:15:21,423
Today?

229
00:15:21,423 --> 00:15:22,643
Okay.

230
00:15:28,093 --> 00:15:30,273
What? Where are you going?

231
00:15:30,273 --> 00:15:32,493
- Is this it?
- Why is she so shy?

232
00:15:32,493 --> 00:15:34,163
Am I supposed to stay longer?

233
00:15:34,833 --> 00:15:36,963
Should I stay longer?

234
00:15:36,963 --> 00:15:39,143
- What?
- Nothing...

235
00:15:40,393 --> 00:15:42,403
People are like this at my work.

236
00:15:42,403 --> 00:15:44,953
They only ask about my schedule and leave.

237
00:15:49,423 --> 00:15:51,813
It's like he's doing a photoshoot.

238
00:15:53,713 --> 00:15:55,183
Want to go on a date today?

239
00:15:55,183 --> 00:15:57,193
- Want to go on a date today?
- Yes.

240
00:15:57,193 --> 00:15:58,773
Sounds good.

241
00:15:58,773 --> 00:16:01,913
What should we do? Is there
something you want to do?

242
00:16:05,883 --> 00:16:08,123
Yu Gyeong is checked out.

243
00:16:09,443 --> 00:16:11,433
Hi.

244
00:16:11,433 --> 00:16:14,733
- It's Jun Hyeon.
- Well... Are you...

245
00:16:16,723 --> 00:16:17,983
Huh?

246
00:16:20,323 --> 00:16:22,193
I want to go on a date with you.

247
00:16:22,193 --> 00:16:24,133
- "I want to go on a date with you."
- Was I supposed to say more?

248
00:16:24,133 --> 00:16:25,523
No, no, no.

249
00:16:25,523 --> 00:16:28,093
Wasn't that manly?

250
00:16:32,713 --> 00:16:33,973
[Glancing]

251
00:16:34,593 --> 00:16:36,803
Isn't that Seong Min in the background?

252
00:16:39,713 --> 00:16:41,593
Shut the door, Seong Min.

253
00:16:43,793 --> 00:16:46,193
Oppa, where were you?

254
00:16:46,193 --> 00:16:47,233
Huh?

255
00:16:47,233 --> 00:16:49,993
- He can hear her.
- He needs to hear it.

256
00:16:49,993 --> 00:16:52,463
I think this is where you ask someone out.

257
00:16:52,463 --> 00:16:55,943
- Really?
- It has a serious atmosphere.

258
00:16:55,943 --> 00:16:56,953
Let's have a coffee.

259
00:16:56,953 --> 00:16:59,763
- Nice, nice.
- This is nice.

260
00:17:00,913 --> 00:17:02,723
What are you doing today?

261
00:17:02,723 --> 00:17:05,413
- Nothing.
- You're not doing anything?

262
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:07,653
Want to go on a date with me?

263
00:17:07,653 --> 00:17:09,473
Of course.

264
00:17:12,433 --> 00:17:14,333
Gosh, Yu Gyeong.

265
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:18,733
[She leaves the room
after waiting for someone]

266
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:22,673
- Hi.
- Hi.

267
00:17:22,673 --> 00:17:24,133
- Are you eating?
- Huh?

268
00:17:24,133 --> 00:17:25,783
- Are you eating?
- Yes.

269
00:17:25,783 --> 00:17:30,273
I want to have galbijjim,
but everyone's going on a date.

270
00:17:33,283 --> 00:17:35,903
- What are you doing today?
- Nothing.

271
00:17:38,123 --> 00:17:40,853
- What about you?
- Me, too.

272
00:17:42,433 --> 00:17:45,033
Seriously?

273
00:17:45,033 --> 00:17:47,793
Let's do that for now.

274
00:17:48,773 --> 00:17:50,573
Do you want to eat something?

275
00:17:51,483 --> 00:17:53,183
- Is that okay?
- Yes.

276
00:17:53,183 --> 00:17:55,443
What do we do?

277
00:17:56,463 --> 00:17:57,563
What a chaos.

278
00:17:57,563 --> 00:17:59,653
You have to eat it while it's still crunchy.

279
00:17:59,653 --> 00:18:01,263
I like it when it softens up.

280
00:18:01,263 --> 00:18:04,053
- Crazy.
- It softens quickly.

281
00:18:04,053 --> 00:18:05,323
Yes.

282
00:18:06,273 --> 00:18:08,823
Can Wu Yeol do that?

283
00:18:11,023 --> 00:18:15,893
[Which way will Yu Gyeong's heart go toward?]

284
00:18:18,363 --> 00:18:21,073
Let's talk outside.

285
00:18:23,403 --> 00:18:28,443
For today's date...

286
00:18:28,443 --> 00:18:30,643
It's as I said yesterday.

287
00:18:31,583 --> 00:18:33,033
So...

288
00:18:40,003 --> 00:18:41,443
So...

289
00:18:51,853 --> 00:18:53,913
Are you going out with Gyu Ri?

290
00:18:55,243 --> 00:18:57,283
There are things I said, too.

291
00:18:59,593 --> 00:19:03,283
I don't know if it will be today or tomorrow.

292
00:19:07,913 --> 00:19:10,823
I was supposed to go on a date with Gyu Ri

293
00:19:12,433 --> 00:19:16,053
at least three times.

294
00:19:16,053 --> 00:19:18,903
- Why?
- Because of what I said.

295
00:19:19,763 --> 00:19:21,723
Who cares?

296
00:19:26,513 --> 00:19:27,843
Okay.

297
00:19:27,843 --> 00:19:29,113
But...

298
00:19:29,953 --> 00:19:36,663
I thought about it for two hours
before going to bed.

299
00:19:36,663 --> 00:19:39,143
I think that's the right thing to do.

300
00:19:40,083 --> 00:19:42,583
In this situation,

301
00:19:42,583 --> 00:19:44,213
Yes.

302
00:19:44,213 --> 00:19:49,013
I thought things might get difficult
for you as time goes by.

303
00:19:55,763 --> 00:19:59,133
Yes, okay.

304
00:19:59,133 --> 00:20:00,563
But...

305
00:20:07,713 --> 00:20:10,473
what I'm thinking right now is...

306
00:20:15,423 --> 00:20:18,683
To be honest, I'm a bit...

307
00:20:19,863 --> 00:20:22,523
I think I should just stay out.

308
00:20:23,213 --> 00:20:24,503
Huh?

309
00:20:26,143 --> 00:20:27,603
Right now,

310
00:20:28,703 --> 00:20:32,013
I'm not sure how I feel.

311
00:20:32,013 --> 00:20:34,893
Of course, I'm a bit mad at you.

312
00:20:35,813 --> 00:20:44,183
I'll put aside
the original feelings I've had.

313
00:20:51,893 --> 00:20:57,853
Just by seeing
how you are behaving right now...

314
00:20:59,873 --> 00:21:01,903
I think I'll be okay.

315
00:21:15,413 --> 00:21:20,693
[There is silence between them]

316
00:21:23,103 --> 00:21:26,843
Are you saying then...

317
00:21:28,193 --> 00:21:29,473
well...

318
00:21:31,233 --> 00:21:34,533
you think there isn't much you can do.

319
00:21:34,533 --> 00:21:35,483
Yes.

320
00:21:35,483 --> 00:21:37,273
And so...

321
00:21:47,653 --> 00:21:53,923
did you think it was over at this point?

322
00:21:53,923 --> 00:21:56,783
Is he really asking her that?

323
00:22:01,243 --> 00:22:03,783
I have thought that.

324
00:22:06,833 --> 00:22:08,993
I did think that.

325
00:22:08,993 --> 00:22:11,453
- Of course, I did.
- Right now...

326
00:22:14,193 --> 00:22:17,563
I know I shouldn't be saying this,

327
00:22:18,403 --> 00:22:20,923
but I think it's all my fault.

328
00:22:22,033 --> 00:22:24,853
I don't know. I don't know...

329
00:22:26,213 --> 00:22:28,673
why you're confused.

330
00:22:31,203 --> 00:22:34,583
- It might be hard to understand.
- I don't understand.

331
00:22:38,533 --> 00:22:44,683
From my perspective,
you already are beyond my reach.

332
00:22:44,683 --> 00:22:46,303
She reached a conclusion.

333
00:22:46,303 --> 00:22:49,363
What am I supposed to say to that?

334
00:22:50,353 --> 00:22:52,963
No, that's not how I felt.

335
00:23:02,023 --> 00:23:06,183
Things are definitely different here.

336
00:23:06,183 --> 00:23:12,363
Try to give yourself a break.

337
00:23:12,363 --> 00:23:14,413
I can't think that.

338
00:23:18,483 --> 00:23:22,563
I'll be the one who can't accept it.

339
00:23:25,193 --> 00:23:30,083
I asked you out, but I'm not sure
if we should go on a date.

340
00:23:30,083 --> 00:23:32,623
- Aigoo.
- What a mess.

341
00:23:32,623 --> 00:23:39,813
I am not sure
if I can make this a pleasant date.

342
00:23:42,903 --> 00:23:45,323
Good luck finding your other half.

343
00:23:45,323 --> 00:23:47,113
My gosh.

344
00:23:48,103 --> 00:23:51,593
I'm wishing you good luck.
You're searching for one.

345
00:23:52,723 --> 00:23:54,893
I'm not telling you to leave.

346
00:23:54,893 --> 00:23:56,993
Well...

347
00:23:56,993 --> 00:23:59,043
He's flustered.

348
00:24:09,873 --> 00:24:11,333
Let's go.

349
00:24:15,013 --> 00:24:17,033
Wow, really?

350
00:24:17,803 --> 00:24:18,543
Let's talk a bit.

351
00:24:18,543 --> 00:24:20,993
- Oh, my God.
- She's mad.

352
00:24:24,913 --> 00:24:25,743
Right here?

353
00:24:25,743 --> 00:24:27,633
No, I...

354
00:24:28,453 --> 00:24:30,023
Well, do you have a lot to say?

355
00:24:30,023 --> 00:24:32,253
I think that was plenty.

356
00:24:35,763 --> 00:24:37,323
Is that so?

357
00:24:39,823 --> 00:24:42,663
It'll be just a second.

358
00:24:44,533 --> 00:24:46,843
What a disaster.

359
00:24:50,773 --> 00:24:52,293
Aigoo, gosh.

360
00:24:52,293 --> 00:24:55,203
[They happened
to overhear their conversation]

361
00:24:55,203 --> 00:24:56,903
It must be awkward.

362
00:25:25,133 --> 00:25:27,223
I'm curious how you feel, too.

363
00:25:28,553 --> 00:25:30,923
How you really feel.

364
00:25:33,533 --> 00:25:38,213
I obviously don't have things sorted out yet.

365
00:25:43,353 --> 00:25:47,533
I like someone who's devoted to me, too.

366
00:25:47,533 --> 00:25:49,063
Right.

367
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:54,453
I think I need to think more.

368
00:25:56,473 --> 00:25:59,683
I'm sure you're stressed about some things.

369
00:26:01,903 --> 00:26:06,743
- No, I'm not really.
- No, but...

370
00:26:06,743 --> 00:26:10,643
shouldn't you feel guilty toward me?

371
00:26:10,643 --> 00:26:12,993
She's right. She's right.

372
00:26:12,993 --> 00:26:14,663
I feel bad.

373
00:26:19,843 --> 00:26:22,553
But I thought saying sorry

374
00:26:27,893 --> 00:26:31,133
wouldn't comfort you.

375
00:26:31,133 --> 00:26:35,633
That's why I have been avoiding saying it.

376
00:26:38,783 --> 00:26:43,583
[He didn't want to apologize because
even saying so could've hurt her]

377
00:26:43,583 --> 00:26:46,003
This is driving me crazy.

378
00:26:53,483 --> 00:26:58,633
Even if I told you not to think that way,

379
00:26:58,633 --> 00:27:01,633
you would think it anyway.

380
00:27:05,893 --> 00:27:09,873
You don't have the right to tell me
not to think a certain way.

381
00:27:09,873 --> 00:27:12,123
That's why I'm not.

382
00:27:12,123 --> 00:27:14,553
Yes, say less.

383
00:27:14,553 --> 00:27:17,293
I think I'm just...

384
00:27:18,983 --> 00:27:21,103
very selfish.

385
00:27:21,103 --> 00:27:22,343
Yes.

386
00:27:23,023 --> 00:27:24,563
I'm sorry.

387
00:27:35,113 --> 00:27:39,723
Choose to do
what you think you'd regret less.

388
00:27:39,723 --> 00:27:41,613
I'll do the same.

389
00:27:42,543 --> 00:27:45,873
You're in that process right now.

390
00:27:45,873 --> 00:27:50,393
It's like walking on a thorny field.

391
00:27:54,373 --> 00:27:55,913
Gosh.

392
00:27:56,973 --> 00:27:59,483
After I said that yesterday...

393
00:28:01,153 --> 00:28:05,203
It's true I used strong words yesterday.

394
00:28:05,203 --> 00:28:09,083
I think I was more excited than usual.

395
00:28:10,793 --> 00:28:14,513
But you were supposed to do that yesterday.

396
00:28:14,513 --> 00:28:16,763
- You set the tone.
- He did.

397
00:28:16,763 --> 00:28:18,463
No, I didn't.

398
00:28:18,463 --> 00:28:20,773
I know you wanted to say that.

399
00:28:20,773 --> 00:28:23,103
You should've told her that privately.

400
00:28:23,103 --> 00:28:24,833
Right, right.

401
00:28:24,833 --> 00:28:28,893
I feel like I'm a fool now.

402
00:28:32,183 --> 00:28:33,883
Well...

403
00:28:42,183 --> 00:28:44,763
That breaks my heart a bit.

404
00:28:44,763 --> 00:28:49,153
I want to take back what I said yesterday.

405
00:28:49,153 --> 00:28:51,053
I really wish I could.

406
00:28:51,053 --> 00:28:52,943
You mean the things you said to me?

407
00:28:52,943 --> 00:28:54,803
No.

408
00:28:54,803 --> 00:28:57,523
Not exactly that.

409
00:28:59,263 --> 00:29:04,503
I wasn't trying to deny my time with you.

410
00:29:04,503 --> 00:29:11,493
I've never regretted what I did
with you or on our dates.

411
00:29:13,033 --> 00:29:15,553
It's not regarding those things.

412
00:29:18,933 --> 00:29:24,433
I think I regretted the way
I behaved yesterday a lot.

413
00:29:25,533 --> 00:29:31,713
I thought it was so appropriate
in that moment, but...

414
00:29:31,713 --> 00:29:34,843
It could've kept it to yourself more.

415
00:29:34,843 --> 00:29:38,253
That, too. I just...

416
00:29:41,215 --> 00:29:45,100
I don't want to have a hard time
because of this.

417
00:29:45,100 --> 00:29:47,750
Of course, it must be harder for you.

418
00:29:50,723 --> 00:29:52,773
From the beginning,

419
00:29:55,173 --> 00:29:58,273
I could've only spent time with you.

420
00:30:00,103 --> 00:30:03,273
But since we live together,

421
00:30:04,143 --> 00:30:07,053
we could be influenced by others.

422
00:30:08,693 --> 00:30:12,903
But I think that hurt you the most...

423
00:30:17,184 --> 00:30:19,723
I thought you'd end up struggling
more than I.

424
00:30:19,723 --> 00:30:23,583
That added to my guilt

425
00:30:23,583 --> 00:30:26,203
and everything else.

426
00:30:27,103 --> 00:30:28,663
I think I disliked that.

427
00:30:28,663 --> 00:30:31,903
No matter how hard it is, I can just...

428
00:30:34,963 --> 00:30:38,053
think that way. I can keep it to myself.

429
00:30:38,983 --> 00:30:44,743
I think I'm trying to sort my feelings
quickly because of that.

430
00:30:44,743 --> 00:30:49,813
I thought I should end things
with one person in the end.

431
00:30:50,613 --> 00:30:54,883
I've been thinking
that's what I'm supposed to do.

432
00:30:54,883 --> 00:31:00,403
I don't feel like
I completely understand Gyu Ri.

433
00:31:00,403 --> 00:31:02,273
Okay.

434
00:31:02,273 --> 00:31:06,993
She said 70-80%
and that it's not significant.

435
00:31:06,993 --> 00:31:10,243
She's like, "Depends on how you behave."

436
00:31:12,203 --> 00:31:14,043
And when I see that kind of attitude...

437
00:31:14,043 --> 00:31:20,733
If I had known her outside of the show,
I would've done nothing.

438
00:31:22,283 --> 00:31:25,513
Why should I give my heart
to someone like that?

439
00:31:29,763 --> 00:31:32,773
But I already said all that.

440
00:31:34,333 --> 00:31:37,903
And be like, "I don't think
we need to go on a date."

441
00:31:37,903 --> 00:31:41,733
And cancel my date with her. I can't do that.

442
00:31:43,383 --> 00:31:46,473
There are things I have been saying.

443
00:31:48,563 --> 00:31:52,503
I thought I should be responsible
for what I said yesterday.

444
00:32:00,833 --> 00:32:02,433
But still...

445
00:32:05,643 --> 00:32:08,703
I feel like you're being sincere about this.

446
00:32:18,233 --> 00:32:22,613
I'm not sure if it started in Japan

447
00:32:22,613 --> 00:32:26,313
or after we came back from Japan.

448
00:32:30,023 --> 00:32:31,983
At some point,

449
00:32:34,283 --> 00:32:37,323
I developed strong feelings for you.

450
00:32:37,323 --> 00:32:40,873
All of a sudden, without realizing it,

451
00:32:42,643 --> 00:32:46,853
it became huge, I thought.

452
00:32:48,983 --> 00:32:56,813
That's probably when I realized
that my feelings were sincere.

453
00:32:58,073 --> 00:33:00,033
And...

454
00:33:03,723 --> 00:33:07,873
I'm not used to this side of me, either.

455
00:33:09,103 --> 00:33:13,843
I thought I was expressing my feelings often,

456
00:33:14,913 --> 00:33:17,263
but I realize you didn't feel that way.

457
00:33:17,263 --> 00:33:20,623
So, I decided to be more proactive.

458
00:33:21,483 --> 00:33:24,513
So, you could notice them, but...

459
00:33:26,193 --> 00:33:32,203
But you might think differently
when it's not the case for me.

460
00:33:33,383 --> 00:33:36,003
I just wanted you to know that.

461
00:33:37,773 --> 00:33:39,773
I don't even know what I'm saying right now.

462
00:33:39,773 --> 00:33:41,603
I find myself disgusting.

463
00:33:41,603 --> 00:33:44,003
I'm so disgusted with myself like this.

464
00:33:44,003 --> 00:33:50,423
Everyone feels the same.
We aren't acting like our normal selves.

465
00:33:50,423 --> 00:33:54,433
We keep noticing the sides of us
we can't accept.

466
00:33:56,483 --> 00:33:58,673
That's the hardest part.

467
00:34:04,503 --> 00:34:07,893
- It's this week, Oppa.
- Huh?

468
00:34:09,233 --> 00:34:11,323
The last day.

469
00:34:11,323 --> 00:34:13,923
I know. Just a week left.

470
00:34:17,823 --> 00:34:20,903
Gosh, what am I supposed to do?

471
00:34:20,903 --> 00:34:24,233
Like you said yesterday,

472
00:34:24,233 --> 00:34:26,583
whether you choose Jun Hyeon

473
00:34:26,583 --> 00:34:29,903
or whatever, I can't say anything to you.

474
00:34:29,903 --> 00:34:31,813
Now,

475
00:34:32,863 --> 00:34:34,883
I just...

476
00:34:36,793 --> 00:34:38,993
Yes, tiptoe around me at least.

477
00:34:50,573 --> 00:34:52,533
Do you want to go on a date?

478
00:34:55,363 --> 00:34:58,023
Yu Gyeong is mature.

479
00:34:58,023 --> 00:35:03,203
It sounds like Wu Yeol is planning
to end things with Gyu Ri.

480
00:35:03,203 --> 00:35:08,283
He thinks he should tell Gyu Ri
for Yu Gyeong's sake.

481
00:35:08,283 --> 00:35:11,493
It sounds like he's planning
to end things with her.

482
00:35:11,493 --> 00:35:14,313
If Yu Gyeong didn't have that attitude,

483
00:35:14,313 --> 00:35:17,263
he would have kept being frustrating.

484
00:35:17,263 --> 00:35:21,163
When she said,
"I hope you find your other half,"

485
00:35:21,163 --> 00:35:24,333
that was a huge shock to Wu Yeol.

486
00:35:24,333 --> 00:35:26,023
That was so necessary.

487
00:35:26,023 --> 00:35:31,463
I think Yu Gyeong still likes
Wu Yeol tremendously.

488
00:35:31,463 --> 00:35:33,653
She was throwing a tantrum.

489
00:35:33,653 --> 00:35:35,853
She was like, "You're still looking
for your other half."

490
00:35:35,853 --> 00:35:38,103
That he's still in the process.

491
00:35:38,103 --> 00:35:39,873
She was like, "Good luck."

492
00:35:39,873 --> 00:35:42,643
We'll keep an eye on you.

493
00:35:42,643 --> 00:35:44,313
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

494
00:35:44,313 --> 00:35:47,553
- Min Ju and Jun Hyeon.
- Gosh, let's go.

495
00:35:47,553 --> 00:35:49,333
The shoes look good on you.

496
00:35:49,333 --> 00:35:51,693
Really? Thank you.

497
00:35:52,473 --> 00:35:58,063
Have you mostly dated
someone older or younger?

498
00:35:58,063 --> 00:36:02,303
Everyone's been either plus or minus a year.

499
00:36:02,303 --> 00:36:05,413
- Really?
- Plus or minus one or same age.

500
00:36:05,413 --> 00:36:08,543
Most of them were the same age.

501
00:36:08,543 --> 00:36:12,643
I've liked someone
who's ten years older than me.

502
00:36:12,643 --> 00:36:14,013
Really?

503
00:36:14,733 --> 00:36:16,753
Why? Because he was mature?

504
00:36:16,753 --> 00:36:20,243
I wanted to date someone
who felt like an adult.

505
00:36:20,243 --> 00:36:22,123
Someone I could rely on.

506
00:36:22,123 --> 00:36:24,473
That was why.

507
00:36:24,473 --> 00:36:27,333
You shouldn't get your hopes up too high.

508
00:36:28,483 --> 00:36:31,043
- Are they similar?
- Just because they're older.

509
00:36:31,043 --> 00:36:32,673
They might look that way.

510
00:36:32,673 --> 00:36:37,443
But they could become childlike
when you're alone with them.

511
00:36:37,443 --> 00:36:39,223
That's so true.

512
00:36:39,223 --> 00:36:44,173
So, you shouldn't expect too much.

513
00:36:44,173 --> 00:36:46,203
I think you're right.

514
00:36:48,643 --> 00:36:50,293
[Arrived at the automobile experience space]

515
00:36:59,743 --> 00:37:02,873
- You can drive it.
- There's a place like that?

516
00:37:02,873 --> 00:37:04,863
This suits you so well.

517
00:37:04,863 --> 00:37:06,313
What's this?

518
00:37:06,313 --> 00:37:08,613
What function is that?
Is the side-view mirror inside?

519
00:37:08,613 --> 00:37:10,813
- Wow.
- The side-view mirrors are inside?

520
00:37:10,813 --> 00:37:12,563
It's so nice.

521
00:37:12,563 --> 00:37:16,563
[A perfect game
for the two who enjoy driving]

522
00:37:16,563 --> 00:37:19,803
- That looks fun.
- Looks like you're in a lot of accidents.

523
00:37:19,803 --> 00:37:23,893
[Jun Hyeon is focused on avoiding accidents]

524
00:37:28,743 --> 00:37:30,643
Wow.

525
00:37:30,643 --> 00:37:31,873
Wow, what's this?

526
00:37:31,873 --> 00:37:34,253
We're getting this
because we're in last place.

527
00:37:35,143 --> 00:37:38,173
What? You can't just pass by.

528
00:37:38,173 --> 00:37:40,443
[They're focused on the game]

529
00:37:41,303 --> 00:37:42,803
Yay!

530
00:37:43,643 --> 00:37:46,213
- You're ahead of me.
- I know.

531
00:37:46,213 --> 00:37:47,823
Do better.

532
00:37:48,523 --> 00:37:50,243
This is cool.

533
00:37:51,283 --> 00:37:53,003
Okay.

534
00:37:54,433 --> 00:37:55,553
First, make a V sign.

535
00:37:55,553 --> 00:37:57,373
- Wow.
- They make a nice couple.

536
00:37:57,373 --> 00:37:58,743
What?

537
00:37:59,543 --> 00:38:02,283
That's too old-fashioned. Let's not do it.

538
00:38:02,283 --> 00:38:03,803
Should we do this?

539
00:38:05,653 --> 00:38:07,853
One, two, three.

540
00:38:08,823 --> 00:38:10,513
[Making unique memories with photos]

541
00:38:10,513 --> 00:38:11,333
So nice.

542
00:38:11,333 --> 00:38:13,073
Should we make a heart symbol?

543
00:38:15,933 --> 00:38:18,453
The background is like that.

544
00:38:20,183 --> 00:38:23,443
Morning sunshine vs. evening sunset.

545
00:38:24,213 --> 00:38:26,443
One, two, three.

546
00:38:26,443 --> 00:38:28,483
- Morning sunshine.
- Morning sunshine.

547
00:38:28,483 --> 00:38:29,573
Why?

548
00:38:30,443 --> 00:38:33,873
I like the sunshine. I like the sun.

549
00:38:33,873 --> 00:38:35,203
Look.

550
00:38:36,213 --> 00:38:38,103
So pretty.

551
00:38:38,103 --> 00:38:40,593
The bridge is so pretty, too.

552
00:38:40,593 --> 00:38:43,383
You want to fall into it, don't you?

553
00:38:44,283 --> 00:38:47,113
Why did you say that so happily?

554
00:38:50,733 --> 00:38:52,563
So nice.

555
00:38:55,303 --> 00:39:00,273
[They're looking at the sunset together]

556
00:39:00,273 --> 00:39:03,133
- This is so healing.
- I know.

557
00:39:03,133 --> 00:39:04,843
You found a good place, Oppa.

558
00:39:04,843 --> 00:39:06,793
I didn't know Namyangju was this nice.

559
00:39:06,793 --> 00:39:08,423
It's like a view in New Jersey.

560
00:39:08,423 --> 00:39:11,733
- It's so pretty.
- Tell me how you feel, Oppa.

561
00:39:16,563 --> 00:39:21,753
I think I tried to talk to everyone once.

562
00:39:21,753 --> 00:39:24,093
I was curious about everyone.

563
00:39:24,093 --> 00:39:27,073
Actually, I did leave Yu Gyeong out
on purpose.

564
00:39:27,073 --> 00:39:30,103
From the get-go.
Because the age gap is too great.

565
00:39:30,103 --> 00:39:33,733
- He has mixed feelings.
- And then...

566
00:39:33,733 --> 00:39:38,123
I started noticing Yu Gyeong.

567
00:39:38,123 --> 00:39:40,973
I don't know why. When we're all together.

568
00:39:40,973 --> 00:39:42,713
[Nodding]

569
00:39:44,143 --> 00:39:49,363
That's why I wanted to go on
a date with Yu Gyeong in Japan.

570
00:39:50,223 --> 00:39:55,213
I found her easy to talk to.

571
00:39:55,213 --> 00:40:00,333
Well, that's how I felt.

572
00:40:05,423 --> 00:40:08,723
During the truth game yesterday...

573
00:40:08,723 --> 00:40:11,803
Because of the texts I've been
exchanging with Seong Min,

574
00:40:11,803 --> 00:40:16,393
I assumed he had feelings for me.

575
00:40:16,393 --> 00:40:22,113
But when we were all together
in the house, it didn't feel that way.

576
00:40:25,483 --> 00:40:33,413
I thought it would be more than 50/50.

577
00:40:34,223 --> 00:40:37,083
I wonder if Seong Min doesn't
know how he feels, either.

578
00:40:37,083 --> 00:40:42,993
Or maybe I'm mistaken.

579
00:40:42,993 --> 00:40:47,403
- It must be so confusing.
- Yeah.

580
00:40:47,403 --> 00:40:52,183
But if I went up to him and asked him,

581
00:40:52,183 --> 00:40:54,283
it'd be too tiring and difficult.

582
00:40:54,283 --> 00:40:59,503
Because he got a lot of answers
from Yu Gyeong yesterday.

583
00:40:59,503 --> 00:41:04,843
Asking him now might put
too much pressure on him.

584
00:41:04,843 --> 00:41:09,993
I just feel like I'm taking a break now.

585
00:41:09,993 --> 00:41:11,573
Can't believe she's understanding.

586
00:41:11,573 --> 00:41:16,013
I didn't know you were going through that.

587
00:41:22,813 --> 00:41:25,823
You're very curious about Yu Gyeong.

588
00:41:25,823 --> 00:41:28,573
- You have positive feelings for her.
- Right.

589
00:41:28,573 --> 00:41:32,693
Who else do you have in mind, you think?

590
00:41:32,693 --> 00:41:36,043
- I'm curious.
- Who am I thinking of?

591
00:41:39,013 --> 00:41:42,623
You don't have to tell me
if you don't want to.

592
00:41:51,493 --> 00:41:53,113
Why is he hesitating?

593
00:41:53,113 --> 00:41:56,003
I feel more cautious
because this is one-on-one.

594
00:41:56,003 --> 00:41:58,183
Because...

595
00:42:00,043 --> 00:42:03,223
- It's okay.
- That'd be bothersome.

596
00:42:03,223 --> 00:42:07,693
[They suddenly became quiet]

597
00:42:07,693 --> 00:42:10,193
I thought he was going to say,
"I only have one person."

598
00:42:10,193 --> 00:42:12,623
Why was he so hesitant and couldn't tell her?

599
00:42:12,623 --> 00:42:15,103
Maybe he thinks
it's rude to say that to his date.

600
00:42:15,103 --> 00:42:17,063
Min Ju asked him out.

601
00:42:17,063 --> 00:42:19,423
- He can't be like, "Only Yu Gyeong."
- You're right.

602
00:42:19,423 --> 00:42:22,133
They were still on a date.

603
00:42:22,133 --> 00:42:25,823
That's how Jun Hyeon is.
Gentleman, Jun Hyeon.

604
00:42:25,823 --> 00:42:29,803
- He's tipping his hat.
- He was so hesitant, right?

605
00:42:29,803 --> 00:42:31,813
[A sunny and peaceful day]

606
00:42:34,233 --> 00:42:36,823
- The weather is nice.
- It's So Yun and Seo Won.

607
00:42:36,823 --> 00:42:40,823
- It's nice and cool.
- I hope she shakes up Seo Won.

608
00:42:41,553 --> 00:42:43,813
I feel like I'm going home.

609
00:42:44,533 --> 00:42:46,593
We are. I'm meeting your parents.

610
00:42:46,593 --> 00:42:48,483
I need to introduce myself.

611
00:42:48,483 --> 00:42:50,573
Hello.

612
00:42:51,883 --> 00:42:53,813
It feels weird.

613
00:42:55,313 --> 00:42:57,243
We're here.

614
00:42:57,813 --> 00:43:00,563
[A brunch cafe in Yangjae]

615
00:43:03,023 --> 00:43:05,173
What a nice atmosphere.

616
00:43:05,173 --> 00:43:06,543
[Hahaha]

617
00:43:06,543 --> 00:43:08,433
I know.

618
00:43:10,323 --> 00:43:13,423
These sleeves are cute.
I can put my thumbs through.

619
00:43:14,473 --> 00:43:16,753
How feminine.

620
00:43:16,753 --> 00:43:19,313
[Annoyed]

621
00:43:26,553 --> 00:43:28,213
[Twitching]

622
00:43:28,213 --> 00:43:30,303
They're mirroring each other.

623
00:43:30,303 --> 00:43:32,243
Stop copying me.

624
00:43:32,243 --> 00:43:34,333
- 3, 6, 9. 3, 6, 9.
- 3, 6, 9. 3, 6, 9.

625
00:43:34,333 --> 00:43:35,233
- 1.
- 2.

626
00:43:35,233 --> 00:43:36,303
- 4.
- 5.

627
00:43:36,303 --> 00:43:38,143
They're having fun.

628
00:43:40,183 --> 00:43:41,153
- 40.
- 41.

629
00:43:41,153 --> 00:43:44,023
- 42.
- They're so far along.

630
00:43:44,023 --> 00:43:46,043
They're good.

631
00:43:47,883 --> 00:43:51,143
- That counts as an error.
- What are you saying?

632
00:43:51,143 --> 00:43:53,193
You delayed more.

633
00:43:54,285 --> 00:43:56,270
You'd better get nervous today.

634
00:43:56,270 --> 00:43:58,219
She makes that face
when she has butterflies.

635
00:43:58,219 --> 00:43:59,609
This?

636
00:44:00,798 --> 00:44:02,503
Ready, go.

637
00:44:02,503 --> 00:44:05,323
- What?
- This is heart fluttering somehow.

638
00:44:08,173 --> 00:44:09,023
[Tap]

639
00:44:11,403 --> 00:44:12,773
[Acting innocent]

640
00:44:13,573 --> 00:44:16,033
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

641
00:44:22,213 --> 00:44:23,733
[Staring]

642
00:44:23,733 --> 00:44:28,613
- What's with those eyes?
- Seo Won looks a little nervous.

643
00:44:30,183 --> 00:44:33,053
Are your eyes brown?

644
00:44:33,053 --> 00:44:35,943
She's asking while staring
at him directly. How cute.

645
00:44:35,943 --> 00:44:39,033
Yours are very dark brown.

646
00:44:39,033 --> 00:44:40,963
Like dark reddish brown.

647
00:44:40,963 --> 00:44:43,483
It's almost black.

648
00:44:47,073 --> 00:44:50,023
- Why are they so...
- Lovey dovey?

649
00:44:53,623 --> 00:44:56,763
Why are they acting the same?

650
00:44:59,043 --> 00:45:01,643
She's nervous. So cute.

651
00:45:01,643 --> 00:45:03,653
How strange.

652
00:45:06,693 --> 00:45:08,253
[A table full of English breakfast]

653
00:45:08,253 --> 00:45:10,083
- Thank you.
- So pretty.

654
00:45:10,083 --> 00:45:13,423
- Thank you.
- Looks tasty. What is it?

655
00:45:13,423 --> 00:45:16,033
I'm glad we ordered this.

656
00:45:16,833 --> 00:45:18,663
Whose idea was it?

657
00:45:18,663 --> 00:45:20,443
[Mine]

658
00:45:20,443 --> 00:45:22,973
Good job. It was yours.

659
00:45:22,973 --> 00:45:27,593
She's perfect for men who like older women.

660
00:45:28,983 --> 00:45:31,153
[Staring]

661
00:45:32,083 --> 00:45:34,573
Cut it for her. Cut it for her.

662
00:45:36,433 --> 00:45:38,363
Are you painting?

663
00:45:38,363 --> 00:45:40,053
What's that?

664
00:45:40,053 --> 00:45:42,543
Answer. The map of Korea.

665
00:45:43,613 --> 00:45:45,603
He's funny.

666
00:45:46,393 --> 00:45:49,273
- Give me that.
- Gosh.

667
00:45:49,273 --> 00:45:51,123
This is my first time, too.

668
00:45:51,123 --> 00:45:52,833
I might be worse than you.

669
00:45:52,833 --> 00:45:54,943
I might cut the plate.

670
00:45:56,113 --> 00:45:59,663
You have to follow the grain of the meat.

671
00:46:03,393 --> 00:46:05,373
- Should I cut the egg for you?
- Yes.

672
00:46:05,373 --> 00:46:07,823
I've been waiting for you to say that.

673
00:46:09,723 --> 00:46:11,613
Thank you.

674
00:46:15,203 --> 00:46:18,963
You love meat. Tasty, isn't it?

675
00:46:19,993 --> 00:46:24,553
We only have seven days left now.

676
00:46:24,553 --> 00:46:27,133
What are you most looking forward to?

677
00:46:27,133 --> 00:46:32,033
Getting to know someone I'm interested in.

678
00:46:32,033 --> 00:46:34,193
Growing closer together?

679
00:46:35,333 --> 00:46:41,293
One could say it was brief,

680
00:46:42,783 --> 00:46:47,423
but I think I got to know other people well.

681
00:46:48,503 --> 00:46:53,303
So, the remaining seven days
don't feel too short.

682
00:46:54,923 --> 00:46:58,693
We have tomorrow and the day after, too.

683
00:46:58,693 --> 00:47:02,263
- Right, they still have time.
- Right.

684
00:47:08,183 --> 00:47:10,023
I think there's plenty of time.

685
00:47:10,023 --> 00:47:11,733
- So cool.
- She's so eloquent.

686
00:47:11,733 --> 00:47:15,773
It only takes three minutes to score a goal.

687
00:47:25,673 --> 00:47:27,483
[Smile]

688
00:47:27,483 --> 00:47:30,673
Why are you laughing?
You think I'm funny-looking?

689
00:47:30,673 --> 00:47:33,013
- Am I not allowed to laugh?
- Am I funny-looking?

690
00:47:33,013 --> 00:47:35,203
He knows he's not.

691
00:47:36,763 --> 00:47:38,753
I can't help but laugh when I look at you.

692
00:47:38,753 --> 00:47:42,083
- Gosh, So Yun!
- Seriously...

693
00:47:42,083 --> 00:47:44,383
You're driving me crazy.

694
00:47:45,723 --> 00:47:49,343
She's playing him like a fiddle.

695
00:47:52,253 --> 00:47:58,263
I feel like I'm a little girl
with you sometimes.

696
00:47:58,263 --> 00:48:00,143
Why is that?

697
00:48:00,143 --> 00:48:02,353
I'm not sure.

698
00:48:04,343 --> 00:48:06,743
- Is that a good thing?
- It's a good thing.

699
00:48:06,743 --> 00:48:09,753
I turn into a little girl with you, too.

700
00:48:17,913 --> 00:48:19,673
- She's good at staring.
- Not bad.

701
00:48:19,673 --> 00:48:22,733
- You laugh when you look at me, too.
- You, too?

702
00:48:26,303 --> 00:48:28,143
Laugh?

703
00:48:32,123 --> 00:48:34,293
[Finally, a warm day]

704
00:48:34,293 --> 00:48:36,893
This is the perfect time.

705
00:48:38,843 --> 00:48:40,593
It's like a stream.

706
00:48:40,593 --> 00:48:42,883
- Is it a canal?
- It's a canal.

707
00:48:43,603 --> 00:48:45,243
- You're in trouble, Noona.
- Why?

708
00:48:45,243 --> 00:48:48,953
- You stepped on mud.
- That's nothing.

709
00:48:48,953 --> 00:48:51,433
You're such an interesting character.

710
00:48:52,253 --> 00:48:53,873
You're interesting, too.

711
00:48:53,873 --> 00:48:54,933
- Me?
- Yes.

712
00:48:54,933 --> 00:48:57,093
- How so?
- You're mysterious.

713
00:48:57,093 --> 00:48:59,463
- Mysterious?
- Yes.

714
00:49:02,393 --> 00:49:03,943
Listen.

715
00:49:05,723 --> 00:49:07,743
[Punishing]

716
00:49:09,303 --> 00:49:11,133
Look over here.

717
00:49:11,873 --> 00:49:14,133
You look like a city boy.

718
00:49:16,013 --> 00:49:18,723
You found your signature pose.

719
00:49:19,843 --> 00:49:21,953
[Mimicking]

720
00:49:25,893 --> 00:49:28,533
- Are your feet okay?
- Yes.

721
00:49:28,533 --> 00:49:32,313
Were you going to switch shoes if they hurt?

722
00:49:32,313 --> 00:49:34,473
No, I was going to empathize with you.

723
00:49:34,473 --> 00:49:37,433
I'm an F. "It must hurt."

724
00:49:38,833 --> 00:49:41,753
Rather than just saying that...

725
00:49:41,753 --> 00:49:44,103
- with action...
- Should mine hurt, too?

726
00:49:46,463 --> 00:49:48,113
How about this? How about this?

727
00:49:48,113 --> 00:49:50,203
Hold on. Hold on.

728
00:49:50,203 --> 00:49:52,003
Ready, go.

729
00:49:55,763 --> 00:49:57,773
They're so cute.

730
00:49:58,933 --> 00:50:00,683
Hi.

731
00:50:00,683 --> 00:50:03,623
Should I take one of you, too? Click, click.

732
00:50:03,623 --> 00:50:05,863
There are so many doggies.

733
00:50:05,863 --> 00:50:07,663
Gosh, they're so cute.

734
00:50:07,663 --> 00:50:11,273
What a sweetie. How come he's so sweet?

735
00:50:11,273 --> 00:50:13,743
Give me some love.

736
00:50:13,743 --> 00:50:16,973
- It feels nice. Scratch, scratch.
- That dog is like Seo Won.

737
00:50:16,973 --> 00:50:18,673
I need that on a sign.

738
00:50:20,443 --> 00:50:22,933
"Give me some love."

739
00:50:24,003 --> 00:50:26,023
Give me some love.

740
00:50:26,023 --> 00:50:28,093
So funny.

741
00:50:29,473 --> 00:50:31,623
[The sun is already setting]

742
00:50:32,603 --> 00:50:35,603
[A wine bar]

743
00:50:36,133 --> 00:50:38,093
Let's get a recommendation.

744
00:50:38,093 --> 00:50:41,193
The signature scallop-and-shrimp
stir-fry is popular.

745
00:50:41,193 --> 00:50:43,333
You can't have scallops.

746
00:50:43,333 --> 00:50:45,923
- Should we get the chop steak?
- Gosh, so attentive.

747
00:50:45,923 --> 00:50:48,973
It's touching that he remembers.

748
00:50:53,623 --> 00:50:56,503
- Should I make you a canapé?
- What's going on?

749
00:51:04,373 --> 00:51:06,553
[Goofing]

750
00:51:07,283 --> 00:51:09,013
I was playing.

751
00:51:10,283 --> 00:51:12,323
- Is it good?
- Yes.

752
00:51:19,023 --> 00:51:21,733
- Seo Won is checking her reaction.
- He is.

753
00:51:21,733 --> 00:51:23,853
We had a date today.

754
00:51:23,853 --> 00:51:26,543
Who would you like to choose
tomorrow if you could?

755
00:51:26,543 --> 00:51:28,393
- Tomorrow?
- Yes.

756
00:51:31,683 --> 00:51:34,173
I don't think I have anyone but you.

757
00:51:38,203 --> 00:51:40,523
I knew she would say that.

758
00:51:40,523 --> 00:51:42,073
Yes, sir.

759
00:51:42,073 --> 00:51:44,663
What's familiar is the best.

760
00:51:44,663 --> 00:51:46,053
What?

761
00:51:46,053 --> 00:51:50,033
- Stop doing that.
- Why not?

762
00:51:51,383 --> 00:51:54,823
- You really are a little girl.
- You're making me blush.

763
00:51:54,823 --> 00:51:56,783
He's really like a little girl.

764
00:51:57,813 --> 00:52:01,443
He's never been loved by someone like this.

765
00:52:01,443 --> 00:52:03,333
Right.

766
00:52:14,023 --> 00:52:19,003
I feel more comfortable when I'm with you.

767
00:52:19,003 --> 00:52:22,003
I joke around more, too.

768
00:52:22,973 --> 00:52:26,763
- I thought that was all.
- Oh, my gosh!

769
00:52:26,763 --> 00:52:31,113
But you get me so flustered.

770
00:52:31,113 --> 00:52:32,273
Me?

771
00:52:32,273 --> 00:52:34,153
That's the best.

772
00:52:34,153 --> 00:52:36,473
"You get me flustered."

773
00:52:36,473 --> 00:52:38,973
- Why?
- I don't know.

774
00:52:38,973 --> 00:52:40,983
"You get me flustered."

775
00:52:41,863 --> 00:52:45,433
- You're unpredictable.
- She keeps poking at him.

776
00:52:48,403 --> 00:52:52,113
You're the one who's mysterious to me.

777
00:52:57,693 --> 00:52:59,753
By the way,

778
00:53:01,103 --> 00:53:07,143
I thought you were just
easy to be around, too.

779
00:53:07,143 --> 00:53:10,503
- "I thought."
- When did you change your mind?

780
00:53:13,633 --> 00:53:16,193
It's not anything significant.

781
00:53:16,193 --> 00:53:18,313
There was a moment.

782
00:53:18,313 --> 00:53:23,153
You said you feel hurt when a significant
other stops the cutesy talk after a fight.

783
00:53:23,153 --> 00:53:25,183
Right. I know how that feels.

784
00:53:26,103 --> 00:53:28,523
I think...

785
00:53:29,533 --> 00:53:33,853
I'm moved by someone honest
and pure like that.

786
00:53:33,853 --> 00:53:36,343
Seo Won is like that.

787
00:53:37,593 --> 00:53:39,533
I get so hurt by that.

788
00:53:39,533 --> 00:53:44,743
I think stuff like that affected me.

789
00:53:44,743 --> 00:53:48,193
And whether it's something...

790
00:53:48,193 --> 00:53:52,443
positive or something you want to hide,

791
00:53:52,443 --> 00:53:55,923
you express yourself honestly.

792
00:53:57,073 --> 00:53:59,313
I thought that was very manly.

793
00:54:00,333 --> 00:54:03,093
- I cried a bit, too.
- When?

794
00:54:03,093 --> 00:54:04,883
You cried a bit, too?

795
00:54:04,883 --> 00:54:06,823
I teared up a bit.

796
00:54:08,223 --> 00:54:10,453
I tend to...

797
00:54:11,473 --> 00:54:13,653
try to hide a side of me

798
00:54:14,733 --> 00:54:19,283
I'm embarrassed about from other people.

799
00:54:19,283 --> 00:54:22,533
- Because people can remember.
- That's right.

800
00:54:22,533 --> 00:54:26,303
I think I like someone
who knows how to be honest.

801
00:54:26,303 --> 00:54:29,023
- It's rare.
- It's the most important thing.

802
00:54:32,633 --> 00:54:36,503
When we spoke the truth that day...

803
00:54:36,503 --> 00:54:40,073
You were like, "No, I am 95%."

804
00:54:42,133 --> 00:54:45,393
- You mentioned that.
- That's right.

805
00:54:45,393 --> 00:54:47,193
I only have one person.

806
00:54:47,193 --> 00:54:53,823
My first and second are 95% and 5%.

807
00:54:56,903 --> 00:54:59,633
I was so surprised. It was shocking.

808
00:54:59,633 --> 00:55:03,493
I didn't know anyone could say that.

809
00:55:03,493 --> 00:55:06,173
Right, right.

810
00:55:07,583 --> 00:55:09,863
During the truth game,

811
00:55:11,283 --> 00:55:14,293
when there's nothing wrong with my feelings,

812
00:55:14,293 --> 00:55:19,983
trying to hide them was like lying to myself.

813
00:55:19,983 --> 00:55:22,183
She's so smart.

814
00:55:23,353 --> 00:55:27,213
Although I said that,

815
00:55:27,213 --> 00:55:29,143
I regretted it a bit later.

816
00:55:32,263 --> 00:55:36,533
I thought it could have made
you feel uncomfortable.

817
00:55:39,523 --> 00:55:42,813
You don't have to worry about that.

818
00:55:42,813 --> 00:55:45,783
It's a matter of my feelings.

819
00:55:45,783 --> 00:55:48,123
I can manage that myself.

820
00:55:48,123 --> 00:55:50,163
I think it's cooler to be honest.

821
00:55:50,163 --> 00:55:52,543
Wow, what a great conversation.

822
00:55:52,543 --> 00:55:54,733
That should be my problem.

823
00:55:54,733 --> 00:55:58,093
- So, that's okay.
- That's so Seo Won.

824
00:56:02,283 --> 00:56:06,643
You were asked about the two people
you're most interested in.

825
00:56:06,643 --> 00:56:10,023
And you named Gyu Ri and me.

826
00:56:11,103 --> 00:56:14,343
I was like, "Really?"

827
00:56:14,343 --> 00:56:15,933
Really?

828
00:56:15,933 --> 00:56:20,203
- What do you mean?
- I was like, "Does he mean it?"

829
00:56:20,203 --> 00:56:22,723
That I'm curious about you?

830
00:56:22,723 --> 00:56:25,623
She was so sure it was Gyu Ri.

831
00:56:26,543 --> 00:56:29,063
Why do you think I asked you out?

832
00:56:29,063 --> 00:56:31,623
It's because I was curious about you.

833
00:56:34,993 --> 00:56:42,933
I realized I could be interested in
someone unexpected or opposite of me.

834
00:56:42,933 --> 00:56:44,893
He said he got flustered.

835
00:56:45,563 --> 00:56:46,863
[Smiling]

836
00:56:46,863 --> 00:56:48,743
Does that answer your question?

837
00:56:48,743 --> 00:56:50,593
What do we do now?

838
00:56:50,593 --> 00:56:52,913
That comment makes me feel good.

839
00:56:56,293 --> 00:56:57,953
I love their conversation.

840
00:56:58,573 --> 00:57:00,233
What?

841
00:57:00,233 --> 00:57:02,413
What do you mean, what?

842
00:57:07,003 --> 00:57:09,573
When you just moved in,

843
00:57:09,573 --> 00:57:14,183
there was a Self Talk question about
whom I'm most concerned about.

844
00:57:14,183 --> 00:57:16,883
Everyone has their own pace.

845
00:57:17,963 --> 00:57:21,523
- I hope So Yun adjusts okay.
- So kind.

846
00:57:21,523 --> 00:57:23,643
So Yun...

847
00:57:25,493 --> 00:57:27,753
seems to be having a hard time.

848
00:57:27,753 --> 00:57:31,593
She was the last one to join.

849
00:57:31,593 --> 00:57:37,343
She must have been confused
by going on three dates the next day.

850
00:57:37,343 --> 00:57:41,333
She probably didn't get to know people well.

851
00:57:41,333 --> 00:57:45,283
But finding out their opinions
must have confused her.

852
00:57:45,283 --> 00:57:47,873
He's been thinking about her a lot.

853
00:57:47,873 --> 00:57:52,573
I think So Yun is the one who's
breaking my heart the most now.

854
00:57:54,043 --> 00:57:55,863
How interesting.

855
00:57:57,673 --> 00:58:02,453
I don't think I've ever been
a recipient of people's concern.

856
00:58:02,453 --> 00:58:05,543
Ever since I was young,

857
00:58:05,543 --> 00:58:07,773
people said, "So Yun can manage herself."

858
00:58:07,773 --> 00:58:10,313
Right. She looks like the type.

859
00:58:12,673 --> 00:58:14,413
But it's not necessarily true.

860
00:58:14,413 --> 00:58:17,213
Right, she couldn't even
cut the meat herself.

861
00:58:17,213 --> 00:58:18,293
[Tearing up]

862
00:58:19,183 --> 00:58:21,513
You're bad at cutting meat, too.

863
00:58:22,493 --> 00:58:25,823
It was a difficult part to cut.

864
00:58:31,233 --> 00:58:33,863
What are you doing?

865
00:58:33,863 --> 00:58:36,063
She's so high maintenance.

866
00:58:36,063 --> 00:58:37,703
You're doing this on purpose.

867
00:58:38,633 --> 00:58:40,213
Can you tell?

868
00:58:41,893 --> 00:58:43,803
Look at how they are looking at each other.

869
00:58:43,803 --> 00:58:45,963
That's a green light.

870
00:58:48,033 --> 00:58:51,293
- My head hurts.
- Why?

871
00:58:51,293 --> 00:58:53,173
Why does your head hurt?

872
00:58:54,243 --> 00:58:55,923
Just because.

873
00:59:00,273 --> 00:59:01,933
After chasing one person from behind,

874
00:59:01,933 --> 00:59:05,533
- looking into her eyes and talking is huge.
- Right.

875
00:59:08,423 --> 00:59:10,453
So pretty.

876
00:59:16,373 --> 00:59:19,193
I'm paying for all the games today.

877
00:59:19,193 --> 00:59:21,623
[A nostalgic game]

878
00:59:21,623 --> 00:59:24,203
[Seo Won's talent show]

879
00:59:24,203 --> 00:59:26,393
So cool. Wow!

880
00:59:26,393 --> 00:59:27,723
You did it.

881
00:59:27,723 --> 00:59:30,233
What? Do it faster.

882
00:59:30,883 --> 00:59:32,553
[Adding to the fond memories]

883
00:59:32,553 --> 00:59:35,233
So pretty.

884
00:59:35,233 --> 00:59:37,183
That's so sweet.

885
00:59:37,183 --> 00:59:38,733
[Watching an MMA fight]

886
00:59:38,733 --> 00:59:40,563
Who do you think will win
based on their face?

887
00:59:40,563 --> 00:59:43,303
- Let me see.
- Just look at the face. On the left.

888
00:59:43,303 --> 00:59:45,273
[Goofing around everywhere they go]

889
00:59:46,373 --> 00:59:48,493
Ouch.

890
00:59:48,493 --> 00:59:49,743
[Glancing]

891
00:59:57,863 --> 00:59:59,693
[They look good together]

892
00:59:59,693 --> 01:00:01,963
These two have a good chance, right?

893
01:00:01,963 --> 01:00:05,513
They're much better
than I thought they would be.

894
01:00:05,513 --> 01:00:08,993
His feelings were getting solidified.

895
01:00:08,993 --> 01:00:12,103
He said he had a headache.
That's a huge success.

896
01:00:12,103 --> 01:00:14,483
These expressions mean
he has feelings for her.

897
01:00:14,483 --> 01:00:16,863
- I know.
- It means his heart is fluttering.

898
01:00:16,863 --> 01:00:19,773
It's either 50/50 or 60/40 now.

899
01:00:19,773 --> 01:00:22,043
When he had a date with Gyu Ri,

900
01:00:22,043 --> 01:00:25,813
he was talking the whole time,
asking her opinion.

901
01:00:25,813 --> 01:00:28,173
But their conversation was different.

902
01:00:28,173 --> 01:00:31,323
They were asking each other
a lot of questions.

903
01:00:31,323 --> 01:00:33,173
That has to change his feelings.

904
01:00:33,173 --> 01:00:35,583
And this comment assured him.

905
01:00:35,583 --> 01:00:38,243
She said 95% and 5%.

906
01:00:38,243 --> 01:00:40,243
She gave her certainty.

907
01:00:40,243 --> 01:00:43,333
They don't express
their feelings ambiguously.

908
01:00:43,333 --> 01:00:47,333
They are both straight shooters,
and they get each other.

909
01:00:47,333 --> 01:00:50,843
That's why we find it satisfying to watch.

910
01:00:50,843 --> 01:00:53,653
And wasn't their conversation so healthy?

911
01:00:53,653 --> 01:00:54,683
I like that so much.

912
01:00:54,683 --> 01:00:56,923
That was the most impactful comment.

913
01:00:56,923 --> 01:00:59,763
So Yun said, "I don't think
I have anyone but you."

914
01:00:59,763 --> 01:01:02,173
[So Yun is forging ahead toward Seo Won]

915
01:01:02,173 --> 01:01:04,853
She meant it. She meant it.

916
01:01:04,853 --> 01:01:08,223
- She entered through the gap.
- Totally.

917
01:01:09,133 --> 01:01:11,443
[Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong are on their way]

918
01:01:11,443 --> 01:01:14,473
- We're watching you, Wu Yeol.
- Do you know where we're going?

919
01:01:14,473 --> 01:01:16,823
I don't know.

920
01:01:16,823 --> 01:01:18,943
- Are we taking the car?
- Yes.

921
01:01:18,943 --> 01:01:20,503
We're taking the car.

922
01:01:22,373 --> 01:01:26,633
We'll go to the places I chose today.

923
01:01:26,633 --> 01:01:28,233
Really?

924
01:01:29,203 --> 01:01:30,583
Aren't you tired, Oppa?

925
01:01:30,583 --> 01:01:33,183
Me? No, I'm not. I feel alert.

926
01:01:33,183 --> 01:01:34,793
Really?

927
01:01:35,713 --> 01:01:37,223
The weather is clear.

928
01:01:37,223 --> 01:01:39,843
The highest temperature today is 9°C.

929
01:01:45,123 --> 01:01:50,093
- And I think today...
- We'll smile.

930
01:01:50,093 --> 01:01:51,563
Say goodbye with a smile?

931
01:01:51,563 --> 01:01:53,703
No, no, no.

932
01:01:53,703 --> 01:01:56,403
- Gosh, you scared me.
- That's not what I meant.

933
01:01:56,403 --> 01:01:59,793
- We should have fun.
- Yes, I know.

934
01:01:59,793 --> 01:02:04,343
Since we're spending time together today,

935
01:02:04,343 --> 01:02:07,973
let's pretend like this is our first date
and we don't know each other.

936
01:02:07,973 --> 01:02:10,913
Let's just have light conversations.

937
01:02:10,913 --> 01:02:12,253
I don't want to.

938
01:02:12,253 --> 01:02:14,813
What then? What do you want?

939
01:02:14,813 --> 01:02:16,633
Let's just be the same.

940
01:02:16,633 --> 01:02:20,663
Let's not create rules and act normally.

941
01:02:25,413 --> 01:02:29,163
- Same as usual?
- Same as usual.

942
01:02:33,563 --> 01:02:35,993
- Will you let me do that?
- Of course.

943
01:02:35,993 --> 01:02:37,503
What's this?

944
01:02:37,503 --> 01:02:39,663
I'll let you do anything.

945
01:02:39,663 --> 01:02:41,753
So annoying.

946
01:02:41,753 --> 01:02:43,873
You want me to take it back?

947
01:02:45,763 --> 01:02:49,933
I want us to have fun today
instead of worrying.

948
01:02:49,933 --> 01:02:52,993
You'll probably start worrying tomorrow.

949
01:02:52,993 --> 01:02:55,423
Goodness.

950
01:02:55,423 --> 01:02:57,043
The atmosphere shifted.

951
01:02:59,063 --> 01:03:03,633
When I'm alone, I'll probably

952
01:03:04,873 --> 01:03:08,743
- think on my own.
- Probably.

953
01:03:08,743 --> 01:03:10,063
[Feeling guilty]

954
01:03:10,063 --> 01:03:11,893
Inconsiderate.

955
01:03:11,893 --> 01:03:14,323
You only think about yourself.

956
01:03:14,323 --> 01:03:17,643
And do whatever you want to do.

957
01:03:17,643 --> 01:03:20,543
- You aren't that bad.
- This is hard.

958
01:03:21,563 --> 01:03:24,603
- Aren't I so generous?
- Totally.

959
01:03:24,603 --> 01:03:26,923
Well, you have a big heart.

960
01:03:27,693 --> 01:03:30,783
No, I'm just forgetful.

961
01:03:30,783 --> 01:03:33,473
After a sleep, everything feels like a dream.

962
01:03:33,473 --> 01:03:34,953
It was a dream.

963
01:03:34,953 --> 01:03:36,953
[Angry stare]

964
01:03:36,953 --> 01:03:39,373
You little.

965
01:03:39,373 --> 01:03:41,323
Today...

966
01:03:41,323 --> 01:03:43,313
Don't say anything.

967
01:03:43,313 --> 01:03:47,033
- Let's have a blast today.
- Yu Gyeong is trying to make it work.

968
01:03:47,033 --> 01:03:49,113
I wanted to get fresh air.

969
01:03:49,893 --> 01:03:53,003
I thought if we drove a long distance,

970
01:03:53,003 --> 01:03:55,853
I might suffocate to death.

971
01:03:55,853 --> 01:03:57,573
You mean during our drive?

972
01:03:57,573 --> 01:04:01,483
Yes, if the drive took too long.

973
01:04:01,483 --> 01:04:04,323
I had all sorts of thoughts like that.

974
01:04:04,323 --> 01:04:06,743
[He wants to play music for her]

975
01:04:06,743 --> 01:04:08,243
[Glancing]

976
01:04:08,933 --> 01:04:10,753
I like this song.

977
01:04:10,753 --> 01:04:12,403
So what?

978
01:04:12,403 --> 01:04:14,443
I just wanted to tell you.

979
01:04:25,463 --> 01:04:26,593
[Looks]

980
01:04:26,593 --> 01:04:28,493
He's walking on eggshells.

981
01:04:30,493 --> 01:04:33,663
[Well-behaved]

982
01:04:34,543 --> 01:04:39,163
I want to take back what I said yesterday.

983
01:04:39,163 --> 01:04:40,613
I really wish I could.

984
01:04:46,463 --> 01:04:50,583
But the more I keep running
into these situations...

985
01:05:02,073 --> 01:05:05,153
My feelings were truly sincere
in the beginning.

986
01:05:06,053 --> 01:05:07,373
But...

987
01:05:13,463 --> 01:05:15,393
Her feelings are complicated.

988
01:05:21,053 --> 01:05:26,553
Even if I told you not to think that way,

989
01:05:26,553 --> 01:05:29,083
you would think it anyway.

990
01:05:33,773 --> 01:05:37,833
You don't have the right to tell me
not to think a certain way.

991
01:05:37,833 --> 01:05:39,943
That's why I'm not.

992
01:05:39,943 --> 01:05:41,103
Yes, say less.

993
01:05:41,103 --> 01:05:42,903
say less.

994
01:05:45,973 --> 01:05:47,763
It's bothering Wu Yeol, too.

995
01:05:47,763 --> 01:05:53,033
I'll be adjusting my top all day
because that's the style.

996
01:05:53,033 --> 01:05:57,313
It's not that I have other intentions.

997
01:05:57,313 --> 01:06:01,583
Please understand
I'm just adjusting my attire.

998
01:06:01,583 --> 01:06:04,813
I'm not hitting on you or anything.

999
01:06:04,813 --> 01:06:08,683
I mean, I wouldn't have thought...

1000
01:06:08,683 --> 01:06:09,923
Would I have? If you kept pulling it down?

1001
01:06:09,923 --> 01:06:13,803
I'm giving you a heads up just in case.

1002
01:06:14,713 --> 01:06:18,493
This is my warning. Don't get the wrong idea.

1003
01:06:18,493 --> 01:06:20,413
No hidden agenda.

1004
01:06:20,413 --> 01:06:23,473
Since she wants to look pretty.

1005
01:06:24,563 --> 01:06:26,823
Was I ever in your top two?

1006
01:06:26,823 --> 01:06:28,513
Yes.

1007
01:06:28,513 --> 01:06:30,183
Why not now?

1008
01:06:30,183 --> 01:06:32,773
- What's wrong with you?
- What are you saying?

1009
01:06:32,773 --> 01:06:35,003
I'm questioning her right now.

1010
01:06:35,003 --> 01:06:37,543
Could your feelings still change-

1011
01:06:37,543 --> 01:06:40,103
Is there still room in your heart?

1012
01:06:40,963 --> 01:06:42,533
There was only one person the whole time.

1013
01:06:42,533 --> 01:06:46,133
It was Yu Gyeong.

1014
01:06:46,133 --> 01:06:48,843
[He realized how the other men felt
through the truth game]

1015
01:06:48,843 --> 01:06:50,453
Look at his expression.

1016
01:06:56,553 --> 01:06:58,413
I'm uncomfortable.

1017
01:07:04,643 --> 01:07:07,393
Your day starts early tomorrow, huh?

1018
01:07:07,393 --> 01:07:10,933
Yeah. We'll probably eat lunch first.

1019
01:07:13,123 --> 01:07:16,043
- You sound busy.
- I'm popular.

1020
01:07:16,923 --> 01:07:19,743
Yeah, you're popular.

1021
01:07:19,743 --> 01:07:22,013
Wu Yeol, give it your all.

1022
01:07:22,013 --> 01:07:23,283
Oppa, are you popular?

1023
01:07:23,283 --> 01:07:24,943
No.

1024
01:07:29,103 --> 01:07:30,433
Not at all.

1025
01:07:30,433 --> 01:07:31,383
Really?

1026
01:07:31,383 --> 01:07:35,883
No one would miss me even if
I disappeared for a day or two.

1027
01:07:35,883 --> 01:07:38,533
- That's how unpopular I am.
- He's got to be kidding.

1028
01:07:39,593 --> 01:07:41,173
Not me.

1029
01:07:41,173 --> 01:07:43,783
I mean, I would miss you.

1030
01:07:43,783 --> 01:07:46,213
- Oh, my gosh.
- This is...

1031
01:07:47,593 --> 01:07:50,423
[Glances]

1032
01:08:00,843 --> 01:08:02,793
Do you have plans on Lunar New Year?

1033
01:08:02,793 --> 01:08:04,763
- I don't think so.
- No?

1034
01:08:04,763 --> 01:08:05,983
Yeah.

1035
01:08:05,983 --> 01:08:07,163
Why? What about you?

1036
01:08:07,163 --> 01:08:09,013
Me, neither.

1037
01:08:09,013 --> 01:08:12,513
Does anyone? Gyu Ri will...

1038
01:08:12,513 --> 01:08:13,563
Oh, no!

1039
01:08:13,563 --> 01:08:15,803
He's a bit flustered.

1040
01:08:15,803 --> 01:08:16,473
[Glances]

1041
01:08:24,353 --> 01:08:28,473
Now that I think about it,
us hanging out today

1042
01:08:28,473 --> 01:08:30,303
is only beneficial to you, no?

1043
01:08:30,303 --> 01:08:31,233
[Flustered]

1044
01:08:31,233 --> 01:08:34,013
What a selfish prick!

1045
01:08:34,013 --> 01:08:37,343
- All of a sudden?
- I'm-

1046
01:08:37,343 --> 01:08:39,293
I'm-

1047
01:08:39,293 --> 01:08:41,563
- I'm...
- Dang it!

1048
01:08:43,893 --> 01:08:47,233
I mean, what about my feelings?

1049
01:08:47,233 --> 01:08:48,853
What about my feelings?

1050
01:08:48,853 --> 01:08:53,223
I have to hang on
to this feeling of betrayal.

1051
01:08:53,223 --> 01:08:55,263
What am I supposed to do
if it disappears today?

1052
01:08:55,263 --> 01:08:57,433
What if I really forget?

1053
01:08:57,433 --> 01:08:59,976
- I'm sorry.
- This is only beneficial to you.

1054
01:08:59,976 --> 01:09:01,208
I'm sorry.

1055
01:09:01,208 --> 01:09:03,535
Don't tell me
we're going to the Han River to...

1056
01:09:04,323 --> 01:09:06,293
You'd better watch it.

1057
01:09:07,623 --> 01:09:09,933
I'm kidding. You are valued.

1058
01:09:09,933 --> 01:09:12,853
- I feel uneasy.
- Yeah? Since I might lash out at any moment?

1059
01:09:12,853 --> 01:09:15,103
But it's okay. I'm...

1060
01:09:15,863 --> 01:09:17,193
[Cautious]

1061
01:09:17,193 --> 01:09:19,523
[Shakes]

1062
01:09:20,893 --> 01:09:22,393
Forget it. I already spoke my mind.

1063
01:09:22,393 --> 01:09:25,413
We talked a lot in the tea room.

1064
01:09:27,933 --> 01:09:30,653
I looked completely haggard
when I left the tea room.

1065
01:09:31,863 --> 01:09:33,693
I must've sweated profusely.

1066
01:09:33,693 --> 01:09:34,853
Cold sweat?

1067
01:09:34,853 --> 01:09:36,993
[Cold sweat dieting]

1068
01:09:36,993 --> 01:09:38,913
Oh, no!

1069
01:09:38,913 --> 01:09:41,133
I'm wishing you good luck.
You're searching for one.

1070
01:09:41,133 --> 01:09:45,583
[They're approaching their destination]

1071
01:09:45,583 --> 01:09:47,273
[Have their hearts thawed?]

1072
01:09:47,273 --> 01:09:49,483
- We're almost there.
- Yeah.

1073
01:09:49,483 --> 01:09:54,263
[Yanghwa Hangang Park]

1074
01:09:54,263 --> 01:09:56,553
Watch out. There's someone behind you.

1075
01:10:05,083 --> 01:10:08,643
I love it. I want to walk like this.

1076
01:10:10,493 --> 01:10:11,783
This really is nice.

1077
01:10:11,783 --> 01:10:14,923
I've never been to this side
of the Han River.

1078
01:10:15,763 --> 01:10:17,323
Incredible.

1079
01:10:17,323 --> 01:10:19,943
You chose a nice view.

1080
01:10:21,223 --> 01:10:22,923
You chose well.

1081
01:10:25,853 --> 01:10:27,703
- Are you cold?
- No.

1082
01:10:27,703 --> 01:10:29,803
- Are you all right?
- Absolutely.

1083
01:10:31,873 --> 01:10:35,533
Does this road go all the way?

1084
01:10:35,533 --> 01:10:37,223
I wonder.

1085
01:10:37,223 --> 01:10:39,223
I wish it does.

1086
01:10:40,763 --> 01:10:43,273
- It does. Look over there.
- Yeah?

1087
01:10:43,273 --> 01:10:45,783
I hope it doesn't end.

1088
01:10:50,043 --> 01:10:52,863
It's so nice.

1089
01:10:52,863 --> 01:10:53,903
It really is nice.

1090
01:10:53,903 --> 01:10:57,353
How does the breeze feel?

1091
01:10:57,353 --> 01:11:00,093
- It's really nice.
- Really nice?

1092
01:11:00,093 --> 01:11:01,823
That's good to hear.

1093
01:11:05,043 --> 01:11:06,623
Yu Gyeong has a big heart.

1094
01:11:06,623 --> 01:11:07,463
[Glares]

1095
01:11:07,463 --> 01:11:09,343
[Intimidated by one look]

1096
01:11:09,343 --> 01:11:11,153
She's completely softened up.

1097
01:11:11,153 --> 01:11:13,093
You're so comfortable now, aren't you?

1098
01:11:13,093 --> 01:11:15,323
I should maintain an air of gravity.

1099
01:11:15,323 --> 01:11:18,353
But it's hard to maintain that 50%.

1100
01:11:20,523 --> 01:11:23,073
I almost went up to 60%.

1101
01:11:23,073 --> 01:11:25,513
Sorry, I should've controlled myself better.

1102
01:11:25,513 --> 01:11:29,753
You keep testing your limits today.

1103
01:11:29,753 --> 01:11:32,823
- Sorry.
- I can cross the line, but you can't.

1104
01:11:32,823 --> 01:11:35,403
One thing's for sure.
Yu Gyeong has him hooked.

1105
01:11:35,403 --> 01:11:37,313
Exactly.

1106
01:11:38,183 --> 01:11:42,233
I'm ecstatic to be
calling all the shots today.

1107
01:11:42,233 --> 01:11:43,763
You have the upper hand.

1108
01:11:43,763 --> 01:11:45,663
Did I ever have the upper hand?

1109
01:11:45,663 --> 01:11:47,623
You're a total subordinate.

1110
01:11:47,623 --> 01:11:48,493
- Me?
- Yeah.

1111
01:11:48,493 --> 01:11:50,963
I'm not a subordinate.

1112
01:11:50,963 --> 01:11:53,373
- I can't be classified.
- You can't?

1113
01:11:53,373 --> 01:11:55,983
- I can't be classified.
- No such class?

1114
01:11:56,873 --> 01:11:58,763
It's okay.

1115
01:11:58,763 --> 01:12:02,283
Why? Since I'm beneath you?

1116
01:12:02,283 --> 01:12:03,553
It's okay, Oppa.

1117
01:12:03,553 --> 01:12:05,823
Don't think too hard.

1118
01:12:05,823 --> 01:12:07,213
- I'm scared.
- You are?

1119
01:12:07,213 --> 01:12:09,653
- Why?.
-I'm kidding. I'm not scared.

1120
01:12:10,433 --> 01:12:15,033
Rather, I'm thankful for your playfulness.

1121
01:12:15,033 --> 01:12:17,443
Exactly. He's grateful.

1122
01:12:17,443 --> 01:12:19,023
What?

1123
01:12:19,023 --> 01:12:20,553
I really like this.

1124
01:12:24,513 --> 01:12:28,253
[Smiles return like the warm sunset]

1125
01:12:28,253 --> 01:12:29,923
This is a nice walk.

1126
01:12:31,923 --> 01:12:33,913
My hobby is taking walks.

1127
01:12:33,913 --> 01:12:38,543
The breeze is rather nice.

1128
01:12:38,543 --> 01:12:40,443
Yeah.

1129
01:12:40,443 --> 01:12:41,823
Are you cold?

1130
01:12:41,823 --> 01:12:44,093
No. No...

1131
01:12:46,943 --> 01:12:48,513
They're taking wedding photos.

1132
01:12:48,513 --> 01:12:49,733
Whoa!

1133
01:12:55,283 --> 01:12:58,503
The black dress looks pretty.

1134
01:12:58,503 --> 01:13:00,653
Should we take a photo?

1135
01:13:00,653 --> 01:13:01,983
- Photos?
- Should we take a photo?

1136
01:13:01,983 --> 01:13:04,513
- What kind?
- Of the Han River view.

1137
01:13:04,513 --> 01:13:07,603
- Record a video.
- All right.

1138
01:13:08,773 --> 01:13:10,143
This is how it's done.

1139
01:13:10,143 --> 01:13:12,273
Whoa! I look good.

1140
01:13:13,963 --> 01:13:16,773
Whoa, it looks like an ocean.

1141
01:13:18,343 --> 01:13:19,003
[Looks]

1142
01:13:21,143 --> 01:13:23,043
Say what's on your mind.

1143
01:13:29,123 --> 01:13:30,173
There are too many.

1144
01:13:30,173 --> 01:13:32,323
All right. I'll stop here.

1145
01:13:36,443 --> 01:13:38,893
- Should we head back?
- Okay.

1146
01:13:43,163 --> 01:13:45,703
[A pink glow blankets the sky]

1147
01:13:45,703 --> 01:13:47,823
The sky is pink.

1148
01:13:50,303 --> 01:13:53,083
Nice. It's getting dark.

1149
01:13:56,423 --> 01:13:58,683
I can see the nightscape.

1150
01:14:01,003 --> 01:14:02,273
This is so nice.

1151
01:14:02,273 --> 01:14:03,403
A night drive, huh?

1152
01:14:03,403 --> 01:14:05,443
Yeah, it's like a night drive.

1153
01:14:09,023 --> 01:14:10,993
Oh, right. I bought something.

1154
01:14:10,993 --> 01:14:12,193
What is it?

1155
01:14:13,013 --> 01:14:15,583
When you're tired, chocolate.

1156
01:14:15,583 --> 01:14:17,083
What is that?

1157
01:14:17,083 --> 01:14:18,633
I'll open it for you.

1158
01:14:18,633 --> 01:14:20,713
- Do you want one?
- Yeah.

1159
01:14:20,713 --> 01:14:23,803
I don't give this to just anyone.

1160
01:14:23,803 --> 01:14:26,993
This holds a personal meaning for me.

1161
01:14:26,993 --> 01:14:28,973
Yu Gyeong is actually very expressive.

1162
01:14:28,973 --> 01:14:31,043
Exactly.

1163
01:14:31,043 --> 01:14:32,853
I'll take one right now.

1164
01:14:36,243 --> 01:14:38,423
Good, isn't it?

1165
01:14:38,423 --> 01:14:40,273
She's adorable.

1166
01:14:46,013 --> 01:14:47,523
- It's good, right?
- Yeah.

1167
01:14:47,523 --> 01:14:49,413
- Do you want one more?
- What is it?

1168
01:14:50,243 --> 01:14:51,893
I need to buy it.

1169
01:14:53,023 --> 01:14:56,353
[Yongsan Korean Tavern]

1170
01:14:57,883 --> 01:15:00,263
This looks delicious.

1171
01:15:00,263 --> 01:15:02,073
I'll try a bite.

1172
01:15:02,073 --> 01:15:03,143
[Yum]

1173
01:15:06,643 --> 01:15:08,783
How is it?

1174
01:15:08,783 --> 01:15:09,973
[Crinkle]

1175
01:15:10,863 --> 01:15:14,833
[Yu Gyeong takes a bite, too]

1176
01:15:14,833 --> 01:15:16,533
- It's good.
- Delicious?

1177
01:15:18,823 --> 01:15:20,403
Order everything you want.

1178
01:15:20,403 --> 01:15:21,853
I think this is a celebrity hotspot.

1179
01:15:21,853 --> 01:15:24,813
Yeah. Even Chef Choi Kang Rok came here.

1180
01:15:24,813 --> 01:15:27,413
It's IVE's Liz! Daebak.

1181
01:15:27,413 --> 01:15:28,713
Tsuki!

1182
01:15:29,373 --> 01:15:30,643
Really?

1183
01:15:30,643 --> 01:15:32,113
Oh? Tsuki?

1184
01:15:32,113 --> 01:15:34,743
When did you go around eating delicious food?

1185
01:15:34,743 --> 01:15:36,803
Enough said.

1186
01:15:37,693 --> 01:15:39,593
I can eat an entire bottle of perilla oil.

1187
01:15:40,413 --> 01:15:41,743
Thank you.

1188
01:15:41,743 --> 01:15:44,943
What in the world? What is this?

1189
01:15:45,793 --> 01:15:47,083
How is it?

1190
01:15:52,533 --> 01:15:54,493
[Eyes wide open]

1191
01:15:57,113 --> 01:15:59,933
My eyes just opened so wide.

1192
01:15:59,933 --> 01:16:03,323
Why are these tongs so small?

1193
01:16:03,323 --> 01:16:06,013
You sure you can cut it?

1194
01:16:06,013 --> 01:16:08,853
- What are you doing?
- I just want to move it a little.

1195
01:16:08,853 --> 01:16:11,603
You know these all touch?

1196
01:16:11,603 --> 01:16:14,863
- We were wearing this at Yeongjongdo, too.
- Right.

1197
01:16:14,863 --> 01:16:16,153
Right.

1198
01:16:16,153 --> 01:16:19,933
Use your left hand. I'm holding it for you.

1199
01:16:19,933 --> 01:16:22,153
Oh, no.

1200
01:16:22,153 --> 01:16:25,993
- Complaining.
- Please move in a way I can predict.

1201
01:16:27,103 --> 01:16:28,753
Transparent?

1202
01:16:29,533 --> 01:16:30,843
I'm a transparent guy.

1203
01:16:30,843 --> 01:16:33,183
I think...

1204
01:16:33,183 --> 01:16:34,993
I think it's like that.

1205
01:16:34,993 --> 01:16:38,783
I don't like someone that I can't read.

1206
01:16:38,783 --> 01:16:40,843
I like honesty.

1207
01:16:40,843 --> 01:16:43,293
- Honesty?
- Yes. No matter what.

1208
01:16:43,293 --> 01:16:46,453
Because I'm a little too honest.

1209
01:16:46,453 --> 01:16:49,453
I think you're transparent, Yu Gyeong.

1210
01:16:52,163 --> 01:16:53,533
Are you not?

1211
01:16:54,483 --> 01:16:56,593
I am.

1212
01:16:56,593 --> 01:16:58,783
I'm not good at hiding stuff.
It's so obvious.

1213
01:16:58,783 --> 01:17:01,843
I can see that.

1214
01:17:01,843 --> 01:17:06,053
It made me laugh.

1215
01:17:07,553 --> 01:17:09,843
- You know?
- No.

1216
01:17:09,843 --> 01:17:11,273
What does that mean?

1217
01:17:11,273 --> 01:17:15,063
Seeing that kind of stuff makes me laugh.

1218
01:17:15,063 --> 01:17:17,213
What is it?

1219
01:17:17,213 --> 01:17:19,303
Shall we do cheers?

1220
01:17:19,303 --> 01:17:24,203
I keep saying things like "shall"
in front of you.

1221
01:17:24,203 --> 01:17:27,053
- Didn't I do that in the beginning, too?
- Did you?

1222
01:17:30,013 --> 01:17:32,873
I think I was why. That's why.

1223
01:17:33,653 --> 01:17:35,153
Shy?

1224
01:17:35,873 --> 01:17:38,623
For me, I think...

1225
01:17:41,363 --> 01:17:44,523
- I'm trying to be cute.
- My gosh.

1226
01:17:44,523 --> 01:17:48,963
- Saying "shall we?"
- It feels a little shy.

1227
01:17:50,233 --> 01:17:52,473
I think I did it a lot.

1228
01:17:52,473 --> 01:17:54,563
Shall we eat bungeoppang?

1229
01:17:54,563 --> 01:17:58,033
[He kept repeating for Yu Gyeong

1230
01:17:58,033 --> 01:18:09,813
[Wu Yeol's shy expressions]

1231
01:18:09,813 --> 01:18:11,193
I love it!

1232
01:18:11,193 --> 01:18:13,453
I think you did say that a lot.

1233
01:18:13,453 --> 01:18:16,563
I kept saying "shall we"
without realizing it.

1234
01:18:16,563 --> 01:18:19,023
- It's cute.
- Come on...

1235
01:18:19,023 --> 01:18:21,313
These two...

1236
01:18:21,313 --> 01:18:22,893
It's hot in here.

1237
01:18:23,593 --> 01:18:28,153
I'm feeling a little bit buzzed.

1238
01:18:28,153 --> 01:18:29,293
Really?

1239
01:18:29,293 --> 01:18:31,963
Then, let's stop drinking.

1240
01:18:31,963 --> 01:18:34,233
We should stop.

1241
01:18:34,233 --> 01:18:36,743
Let's go home fully drunk.

1242
01:18:36,743 --> 01:18:40,453
You looked pretty tired yesterday.

1243
01:18:40,453 --> 01:18:42,273
- Yesterday?
- Yes. Was it yesterday?

1244
01:18:42,273 --> 01:18:44,163
When you came home after drinking.

1245
01:18:55,643 --> 01:19:02,553
I tend to be aware of your emotions.

1246
01:19:03,483 --> 01:19:07,503
I check out your expression when you walk by.

1247
01:19:07,503 --> 01:19:13,783
I found myself looking for it
a lot yesterday and today.

1248
01:19:13,783 --> 01:19:16,043
He's being honest.

1249
01:19:16,043 --> 01:19:18,123
Really?

1250
01:19:18,123 --> 01:19:20,473
I kept thinking about it.

1251
01:19:20,473 --> 01:19:24,753
Seeing you not look great bothered me.

1252
01:19:29,533 --> 01:19:35,003
But now that we're out together
this afternoon...

1253
01:19:47,453 --> 01:19:51,433
I think I know how I feel.

1254
01:20:00,473 --> 01:20:04,193
- He knows now.
- Right, he knows.

1255
01:20:05,563 --> 01:20:08,343
I suddenly feel like one bottle isn't enough.

1256
01:20:09,273 --> 01:20:11,123
Should we get more?

1257
01:20:11,123 --> 01:20:13,353
Can we go somewhere else?

1258
01:20:13,353 --> 01:20:14,793
Let's go.

1259
01:20:14,793 --> 01:20:16,583
Do you have a lot to say?

1260
01:20:16,583 --> 01:20:18,873
Do you have something to tell me?

1261
01:20:20,093 --> 01:20:22,263
I have a lot to say.

1262
01:20:27,993 --> 01:20:29,893
I have a lot to say.

1263
01:20:32,183 --> 01:20:33,433
Should we go?

1264
01:20:34,193 --> 01:20:35,593
What should we do?

1265
01:20:35,593 --> 01:20:37,393
Should we get another bottle?

1266
01:20:39,673 --> 01:20:42,643
[They don't want to go home yet]

1267
01:20:42,643 --> 01:20:46,083
Yu Gyeong did a good job
with her words today.

1268
01:20:46,083 --> 01:20:48,253
Yu Gyeong made him say things like that.

1269
01:20:48,253 --> 01:20:51,333
Yu Gyeong is so smart and clever.

1270
01:20:51,333 --> 01:20:54,593
She only pouts the amount a man can handle.

1271
01:20:54,593 --> 01:20:56,553
It's not easy.

1272
01:20:56,553 --> 01:20:57,943
If it's too much, it's not pouting anymore.

1273
01:20:57,943 --> 01:21:00,653
Right, no matter
how wrong the other person is,

1274
01:21:00,653 --> 01:21:02,423
it could get intense.

1275
01:21:02,423 --> 01:21:05,603
But she only pouts the amount he can handle.

1276
01:21:05,603 --> 01:21:08,353
Like this. "I'm sorry." "For what?"

1277
01:21:08,353 --> 01:21:10,153
Then, you have nothing to say.

1278
01:21:10,153 --> 01:21:12,113
You can't say "For what?"

1279
01:21:12,113 --> 01:21:13,633
You should not.

1280
01:21:13,633 --> 01:21:16,233
- "Sorry for what?" "What did you do?"
- Why are you so upset?

1281
01:21:16,233 --> 01:21:20,543
You hear that stuff in life
from time to time.

1282
01:21:20,543 --> 01:21:22,263
Sounds like you're traumatized.

1283
01:21:22,263 --> 01:21:26,033
Wu Yeol is clever, too. He received it well.

1284
01:21:26,033 --> 01:21:29,803
Wu Yeol knows she's not just
an ordinary girl, in a good way.

1285
01:21:29,803 --> 01:21:32,263
He knows Yu Gyeong is not ordinary.

1286
01:21:32,263 --> 01:21:36,983
He decided to let go.

1287
01:21:36,983 --> 01:21:40,043
She very gently said to watch out.

1288
01:21:40,043 --> 01:21:42,083
[Right, right]

1289
01:21:42,083 --> 01:21:45,213
[The next morning]

1290
01:21:53,563 --> 01:21:56,213
[Preparing snacks for Seong Min
before going out]

1291
01:21:58,763 --> 01:22:07,393
[Greek yogurt with plenty of granola]

1292
01:22:10,343 --> 01:22:11,923
- What's that?
- Ta-da!

1293
01:22:11,923 --> 01:22:14,223
Let's eat this and go for a walk.

1294
01:22:14,223 --> 01:22:17,683
Greek yogurt and granola.

1295
01:22:21,163 --> 01:22:23,123
Mmm!

1296
01:22:23,123 --> 01:22:25,333
The yogurt is really strong.

1297
01:22:25,333 --> 01:22:27,283
I like it.

1298
01:22:27,283 --> 01:22:28,913
It's really good.

1299
01:22:28,913 --> 01:22:31,443
It's so good with just this
on top of the yogurt.

1300
01:22:31,443 --> 01:22:34,943
- Isn't it good even without honey?
- Yes.

1301
01:22:40,053 --> 01:22:41,863
[Going through the photo roll]

1302
01:22:41,863 --> 01:22:44,033
These are already memories.

1303
01:22:44,033 --> 01:22:46,403
When was that?

1304
01:22:46,403 --> 01:22:48,553
So annoying!

1305
01:22:48,553 --> 01:22:52,113
- You're surprised every time you see Wu Yeol.
- No!

1306
01:22:52,113 --> 01:22:54,853
His hair looks different.

1307
01:22:54,853 --> 01:22:56,903
What do you mean? It looks the same.

1308
01:22:56,903 --> 01:22:58,943
I like it when he wears his hair down.

1309
01:22:58,943 --> 01:23:01,093
[Definitely prefers his hair down]

1310
01:23:01,093 --> 01:23:03,763
Should we play something else?

1311
01:23:03,763 --> 01:23:05,573
Gallery?

1312
01:23:06,423 --> 01:23:10,033
These paintings look even better

1313
01:23:10,033 --> 01:23:12,533
- on a big TV.
- Right?

1314
01:23:12,533 --> 01:23:15,043
It really looks like a painting.

1315
01:23:16,233 --> 01:23:19,383
What are we doing today?

1316
01:23:20,193 --> 01:23:22,003
Where do you think we're going?

1317
01:23:23,843 --> 01:23:25,033
[Looking closely]

1318
01:23:25,033 --> 01:23:27,033
Daehakro?

1319
01:23:27,033 --> 01:23:28,683
[Grins]

1320
01:23:28,683 --> 01:23:32,213
I haven't been to Daehakro in so long.

1321
01:23:32,213 --> 01:23:36,713
I walk to Gwangjang Market from school a lot.

1322
01:23:36,713 --> 01:23:39,973
Gwangjang Market? To eat?

1323
01:23:39,973 --> 01:23:43,493
- Yes. Korean pancakes...
- So much to eat.

1324
01:23:43,493 --> 01:23:45,973
- You really walk over to eat?
- Yes!

1325
01:23:45,973 --> 01:23:49,783
Kalguksu, twisted doughnuts, hotteok...

1326
01:23:49,783 --> 01:23:51,583
They're delicious.

1327
01:23:51,583 --> 01:23:53,633
He thinks she's so cute.

1328
01:23:53,633 --> 01:23:59,923
[They arrive at an alley in Daehakro]

1329
01:24:02,713 --> 01:24:06,493
- They must be seeing a play.
- What?

1330
01:24:07,373 --> 01:24:09,113
Daebak.

1331
01:24:11,583 --> 01:24:13,623
I'm nervous.

1332
01:24:14,403 --> 01:24:16,923
Show me your ticket.

1333
01:24:19,033 --> 01:24:22,703
- I like collecting tickets.
- Really?

1334
01:24:23,423 --> 01:24:25,503
There's a movie based on this, right?

1335
01:24:25,503 --> 01:24:27,173
- Do you know what the story is?
- No.

1336
01:24:27,173 --> 01:24:28,623
I didn't get to see it.

1337
01:24:28,623 --> 01:24:30,513
Who are they looking for? Gong Yoo?

1338
01:24:30,513 --> 01:24:33,033
- Looking for?
- Their first love?

1339
01:24:33,033 --> 01:24:34,893
I see.

1340
01:24:34,893 --> 01:24:36,383
[Push]

1341
01:24:36,383 --> 01:24:38,133
He put that up?

1342
01:24:38,133 --> 01:24:40,503
It feels different whether that's up or down.

1343
01:24:42,813 --> 01:24:45,933
[The performance
starts with much anticipation]

1344
01:24:45,933 --> 01:24:48,513
Plays are a lot of fun.

1345
01:24:49,683 --> 01:24:53,053
Welcome, audience members!

1346
01:25:00,143 --> 01:25:03,063
- He's self-conscious.
- He's aware of her.

1347
01:25:06,083 --> 01:25:08,653
[Funny]

1348
01:25:12,063 --> 01:25:16,583
[The two of them are fully immersed]

1349
01:25:17,233 --> 01:25:21,633
[The curtain falls]

1350
01:25:27,153 --> 01:25:30,473
- That was good.
- It was.

1351
01:25:30,473 --> 01:25:32,133
Why was that so good?

1352
01:25:33,343 --> 01:25:36,743
I haven't seen a musical like that
in a long time.

1353
01:25:36,743 --> 01:25:38,273
A musical like that?

1354
01:25:38,273 --> 01:25:44,183
Daehakro vibes, good for a date.

1355
01:25:44,183 --> 01:25:47,103
I haven't seen something like that...

1356
01:25:47,103 --> 01:25:51,593
in... 13 years?

1357
01:25:56,913 --> 01:26:00,313
[Staring]

1358
01:26:00,313 --> 01:26:02,623
[Looking over]

1359
01:26:03,973 --> 01:26:05,813
Do you like hotteok?

1360
01:26:05,813 --> 01:26:07,633
I love it.

1361
01:26:07,633 --> 01:26:08,993
Should we have one?

1362
01:26:08,993 --> 01:26:10,393
Sounds good!

1363
01:26:10,393 --> 01:26:12,573
I'm hungry.

1364
01:26:12,573 --> 01:26:14,243
I love it.

1365
01:26:16,153 --> 01:26:21,203
Can I have two honey hotteoks?

1366
01:26:21,203 --> 01:26:25,503
[Hotteok purchased]

1367
01:26:25,503 --> 01:26:28,373
So sweet at the appropriate moment.

1368
01:26:28,373 --> 01:26:32,813
A play and hotteok in winter sounds so good.

1369
01:26:32,813 --> 01:26:36,183
Wow, I love hotteok.

1370
01:26:38,883 --> 01:26:40,833
Thankfully...

1371
01:26:42,413 --> 01:26:45,323
It's not dripping too much with honey.

1372
01:26:45,323 --> 01:26:47,193
You're still eating it?

1373
01:26:48,173 --> 01:26:51,913
This is a scenic route.

1374
01:26:52,943 --> 01:26:55,833
- Great view.
- Right.

1375
01:26:55,833 --> 01:26:57,783
Is it a view of Bukhansan?

1376
01:27:03,853 --> 01:27:07,283
[An Italian restaurant in Seongbuk-dong]

1377
01:27:08,243 --> 01:27:11,003
We're always so luxurious.

1378
01:27:11,003 --> 01:27:13,153
He's much older.

1379
01:27:20,363 --> 01:27:22,823
This looks good.

1380
01:27:23,623 --> 01:27:26,343
- What would you like?
- The dotori noodles.

1381
01:27:26,343 --> 01:27:30,433
The gnocchi, and two glasses
of non-alcoholic wine.

1382
01:27:30,433 --> 01:27:31,973
Looks so good!

1383
01:27:31,973 --> 01:27:33,763
It smells amazing.

1384
01:27:33,763 --> 01:27:35,773
Thank you.

1385
01:27:35,773 --> 01:27:38,943
I didn't even think about it,
but this is pork cutlet.

1386
01:27:38,943 --> 01:27:42,003
Right. It's bone-in, too.

1387
01:27:43,133 --> 01:27:46,313
- Let me try.
- Thank you.

1388
01:27:48,123 --> 01:27:50,733
Thanks.

1389
01:27:52,323 --> 01:27:54,763
This is the best part.

1390
01:27:56,913 --> 01:28:00,503
I had a question while watching the show.

1391
01:28:00,503 --> 01:28:03,333
You finally have a question for me?

1392
01:28:04,303 --> 01:28:06,303
No...

1393
01:28:06,303 --> 01:28:10,413
It was about first love, right?

1394
01:28:10,413 --> 01:28:13,003
Right. But he ran away from it.

1395
01:28:13,003 --> 01:28:14,843
Because he might get hurt.

1396
01:28:15,623 --> 01:28:19,323
- A little?
- I actually lost the plot at some point.

1397
01:28:19,323 --> 01:28:21,463
Wow, these two.

1398
01:28:21,463 --> 01:28:24,573
I kept thinking there would
be a hint coming up soon.

1399
01:28:24,573 --> 01:28:28,253
Right, I zoned out when they were
saying the most important thing.

1400
01:28:28,253 --> 01:28:30,993
It's okay. I did the same.

1401
01:28:30,993 --> 01:28:34,053
These two get along so well.

1402
01:28:34,053 --> 01:28:35,643
Neither of them pays close attention.

1403
01:28:35,643 --> 01:28:37,493
Right, this moment.

1404
01:28:37,493 --> 01:28:40,803
[A familiar scene]

1405
01:28:42,553 --> 01:28:44,533
Anyway,

1406
01:28:44,533 --> 01:28:47,693
what do you think first love is?

1407
01:28:47,693 --> 01:28:49,553
First love?

1408
01:28:50,393 --> 01:28:52,243
First love...

1409
01:28:53,893 --> 01:29:00,633
I think I've just had my first love.

1410
01:29:00,633 --> 01:29:02,283
Really?

1411
01:29:02,283 --> 01:29:04,083
I think it fits every criterion.

1412
01:29:04,083 --> 01:29:10,373
My first serious relationship...

1413
01:29:10,373 --> 01:29:15,553
It started when I was really young.

1414
01:29:16,853 --> 01:29:21,443
Someone who knew me the best
during that time.

1415
01:29:28,293 --> 01:29:33,543
As for me, when I think of first love,

1416
01:29:33,543 --> 01:29:36,263
I think I would know.

1417
01:29:36,263 --> 01:29:40,313
While dating, or crushing on each other...

1418
01:29:41,483 --> 01:29:44,063
I don't think I've felt it.

1419
01:29:44,063 --> 01:29:46,613
- Not at all?
- Understandable.

1420
01:29:46,613 --> 01:29:49,703
I'm saving it.

1421
01:29:49,703 --> 01:29:52,473
"You're not my first love!"

1422
01:29:54,203 --> 01:29:57,523
I don't think my first relationship is
necessarily my first love.

1423
01:29:57,523 --> 01:29:59,333
Of course not.

1424
01:30:00,373 --> 01:30:03,113
She's mature for not having experienced it.

1425
01:30:04,043 --> 01:30:06,613
Real love...

1426
01:30:14,233 --> 01:30:22,533
Liking someone very purely.

1427
01:30:22,533 --> 01:30:25,323
I think that's what first love is.

1428
01:30:25,323 --> 01:30:28,543
She's going through it on Heart Signal.

1429
01:30:33,733 --> 01:30:36,163
- Jun Hyeon is so shy.
- I know.

1430
01:30:36,163 --> 01:30:39,803
- So different from when he's with others.
- Because he likes her.

1431
01:30:42,923 --> 01:30:45,513
What do you think of fate?

1432
01:30:45,513 --> 01:30:47,823
Theory of fate?

1433
01:30:47,823 --> 01:30:50,633
I used to believe in it.

1434
01:30:50,633 --> 01:30:52,523
But these days,

1435
01:30:54,783 --> 01:30:58,153
when it comes to meeting people,

1436
01:30:58,153 --> 01:31:03,043
things change based on how I behave.

1437
01:31:03,043 --> 01:31:08,043
I think I tend to think more
realistically these days.

1438
01:31:13,213 --> 01:31:14,633
Same here.

1439
01:31:14,633 --> 01:31:20,143
But they say "love is timing."

1440
01:31:20,143 --> 01:31:22,183
- Do you relate to that?
- Totally.

1441
01:31:22,183 --> 01:31:23,283
Totally?

1442
01:31:23,283 --> 01:31:24,863
I never used to.

1443
01:31:24,863 --> 01:31:28,703
But these days, I think I do.

1444
01:31:30,663 --> 01:31:33,673
Even if the best person approaches me,

1445
01:31:34,543 --> 01:31:40,113
if I don't have time, or can't see
them for some reason,

1446
01:31:40,113 --> 01:31:42,113
I may not recognize it.

1447
01:31:42,113 --> 01:31:44,513
- Right.
- Your fate changes.

1448
01:31:48,833 --> 01:31:52,713
- Right.
- I think that's what timing is.

1449
01:31:57,663 --> 01:32:00,193
With the remaining week...

1450
01:32:00,193 --> 01:32:03,283
- They have a week left?
- We're almost done.

1451
01:32:03,283 --> 01:32:06,063
I'm just not going
to think about it too much.

1452
01:32:06,813 --> 01:32:08,623
Jun Hyeon is such a great guy.

1453
01:32:08,623 --> 01:32:10,483
He keeps telling her how he feels.

1454
01:32:11,363 --> 01:32:12,483
[Staring]

1455
01:32:13,463 --> 01:32:17,993
I'm the most curious about you,
and I like talking to you the best.

1456
01:32:21,273 --> 01:32:25,553
I have fun spending time with you,
and that's enough.

1457
01:32:25,553 --> 01:32:28,493
I hope you have fun when we're together.

1458
01:32:29,323 --> 01:32:30,743
That's where I'm at.

1459
01:32:30,743 --> 01:32:33,693
- What a nice guy.
- He doesn't pressure her.

1460
01:32:33,693 --> 01:32:35,343
I've only had eyes for one person.

1461
01:32:35,343 --> 01:32:38,953
Yu Gyeong.

1462
01:32:38,953 --> 01:32:43,063
[Someone who always quietly watched over her]

1463
01:32:44,153 --> 01:32:46,763
I would be so thankful.

1464
01:32:46,763 --> 01:32:48,183
- How's this? The stick??
- It's good.

1465
01:32:48,183 --> 01:32:50,913
It's a little less...

1466
01:32:50,913 --> 01:32:52,813
There's nowhere to grab.

1467
01:32:56,253 --> 01:33:00,453
[Can his steady feelings]

1468
01:33:00,453 --> 01:33:05,713
[Turn into fate?]

1469
01:33:05,713 --> 01:33:08,113
Wow, daebak.

1470
01:33:09,083 --> 01:33:11,103
[A spot with a wall full
of LPs and tasteful music]

1471
01:33:11,103 --> 01:33:13,103
It's warm in here.

1472
01:33:13,103 --> 01:33:14,793
The vibes.

1473
01:33:18,823 --> 01:33:21,573
[They order non-alcoholic cocktails]

1474
01:33:23,403 --> 01:33:27,013
Do you listen to LPs much?

1475
01:33:27,013 --> 01:33:31,113
I don't get to often.
Sometimes in places like this.

1476
01:33:31,113 --> 01:33:33,613
Should we request songs?

1477
01:33:33,613 --> 01:33:34,523
Do you have any?

1478
01:33:34,523 --> 01:33:36,573
I don't know. I don't know what they have.

1479
01:33:36,573 --> 01:33:37,853
They'll play what you want.

1480
01:33:37,853 --> 01:33:39,673
Let me look it up.

1481
01:33:39,673 --> 01:33:44,053
"Songs you must listen to at an LP bar."

1482
01:33:44,053 --> 01:33:46,203
What a good idea.

1483
01:33:46,203 --> 01:33:48,473
So cute.

1484
01:33:49,303 --> 01:33:51,253
I know what I want. I found something.

1485
01:33:51,253 --> 01:33:53,983
I like this song.

1486
01:33:53,983 --> 01:33:55,573
[Glancing]

1487
01:33:59,243 --> 01:34:00,613
Is it...

1488
01:34:00,613 --> 01:34:02,623
[Looks like she found the post
on Naver Knowledge]

1489
01:34:02,623 --> 01:34:04,143
No...

1490
01:34:04,143 --> 01:34:06,213
Did you find it on Naver Knowledge?

1491
01:34:06,213 --> 01:34:08,773
I did look it up, but...

1492
01:34:08,773 --> 01:34:10,833
Really?

1493
01:34:10,833 --> 01:34:13,183
Neither of them is very cultured.

1494
01:34:14,193 --> 01:34:15,173
I looked it up.

1495
01:34:15,173 --> 01:34:19,963
- Are you the one who asked this?
- It was on the list already.

1496
01:34:19,963 --> 01:34:21,373
I did see the post.

1497
01:34:21,373 --> 01:34:23,273
It reminded me.

1498
01:34:23,273 --> 01:34:25,833
- Crazy.
- You found it immediately.

1499
01:34:28,253 --> 01:34:29,903
[Successfully requests the song
after some chaos]

1500
01:34:29,903 --> 01:34:32,653
Is he not going to do this?

1501
01:34:33,573 --> 01:34:35,683
We're here for fun, so...

1502
01:34:35,683 --> 01:34:37,003
Sure.

1503
01:34:40,063 --> 01:34:42,633
[Jun Hyeon requests
"Don't Look Back In Anger"]

1504
01:34:42,633 --> 01:34:44,573
Here we go.

1505
01:34:55,323 --> 01:34:59,413
I'm no fun. My life is no fun.

1506
01:34:59,413 --> 01:35:01,763
How about your partner?

1507
01:35:01,763 --> 01:35:03,333
Do you want your partner to be like that?

1508
01:35:03,333 --> 01:35:05,553
- A little bit?
- Really?

1509
01:35:07,653 --> 01:35:10,943
Looking at my personality and preferences,

1510
01:35:10,943 --> 01:35:14,123
if someone is way too into
something, they don't suit me.

1511
01:35:14,123 --> 01:35:15,613
Sure.

1512
01:35:16,483 --> 01:35:17,663
Then, it's Jun Hyeon.

1513
01:35:17,663 --> 01:35:20,423
That sounds like Jun Hyeon. So relaxed.

1514
01:35:20,423 --> 01:35:24,203
My honest concern is... I'm no fun.

1515
01:35:24,203 --> 01:35:25,523
But...

1516
01:35:26,933 --> 01:35:29,963
- Your life?
- Everyone else has a hobby and such.

1517
01:35:29,963 --> 01:35:33,393
When I ask them, they're like, "I do this."

1518
01:35:34,303 --> 01:35:36,923
So, I pushed myself to think of something.

1519
01:35:36,923 --> 01:35:38,353
But...

1520
01:35:40,493 --> 01:35:42,783
I guess there's no need.

1521
01:35:42,783 --> 01:35:45,653
- He's saying that?
- That's so nice.

1522
01:35:47,393 --> 01:35:52,743
The two of us don't need to do anything.

1523
01:35:54,433 --> 01:35:57,123
We're like people low on phone battery.

1524
01:36:02,033 --> 01:36:05,713
[The day these two were alone in the house]

1525
01:36:07,033 --> 01:36:08,703
This is hard.

1526
01:36:08,703 --> 01:36:10,243
A, A, A, A!

1527
01:36:10,243 --> 01:36:12,013
Do it. Pick now.

1528
01:36:12,013 --> 01:36:14,683
You can't stop.

1529
01:36:14,683 --> 01:36:18,413
[The two had fun
without doing anything special]

1530
01:36:18,413 --> 01:36:21,323
He's her ideal type. Daebak.

1531
01:36:25,413 --> 01:36:27,433
I think you're so brave.

1532
01:36:27,433 --> 01:36:29,933
Me? I'm not brave.

1533
01:36:29,933 --> 01:36:31,553
I think you are.

1534
01:36:32,223 --> 01:36:33,893
So cool.

1535
01:36:41,493 --> 01:36:43,823
I don't do any of that stuff.

1536
01:36:43,823 --> 01:36:45,533
Stocks or...

1537
01:36:45,533 --> 01:36:49,043
- Not at all?
- Stuff like that.

1538
01:36:49,043 --> 01:36:52,643
I just don't like thinking
about that kind of thing.

1539
01:36:53,593 --> 01:37:00,283
Focusing on my own work
is a better use of my time.

1540
01:37:00,283 --> 01:37:03,773
I've never done anything like that
in my life.

1541
01:37:03,773 --> 01:37:05,753
Daebak. That's unexpected.

1542
01:37:08,753 --> 01:37:10,653
I know I'm no fun.

1543
01:37:14,923 --> 01:37:16,233
Do you like Waterbomb?

1544
01:37:16,233 --> 01:37:17,793
I've never been.

1545
01:37:18,923 --> 01:37:20,453
So embarrassing.

1546
01:37:20,453 --> 01:37:22,813
I really like him.

1547
01:37:22,813 --> 01:37:25,833
They know each other,
so they can joke about it.

1548
01:37:25,833 --> 01:37:30,263
I think I'm just going to combust like this.

1549
01:37:30,263 --> 01:37:32,023
Just lying in bed?

1550
01:37:32,023 --> 01:37:34,133
You're just waiting to be a grandma.

1551
01:37:34,133 --> 01:37:36,763
When you're a grandma,
it's legal to do nothing.

1552
01:37:36,763 --> 01:37:40,843
[The night deepens with their stories]

1553
01:37:46,163 --> 01:37:49,093
This is my favorite neighborhood.

1554
01:37:49,093 --> 01:37:50,113
Gyeongbokgung?

1555
01:37:50,113 --> 01:37:52,303
Oh, really?

1556
01:37:52,303 --> 01:37:57,653
I once stubbornly walked it
in the dead of winter.

1557
01:37:57,653 --> 01:38:01,533
Nice. That's not stubborn. That's romantic.

1558
01:38:01,533 --> 01:38:03,473
Right. I was listening to music by myself.

1559
01:38:03,473 --> 01:38:06,043
I love it here.

1560
01:38:06,043 --> 01:38:08,213
Here? The Yi Sun Sin statue?

1561
01:38:08,213 --> 01:38:11,253
Yes. I love General Yi Sun Sin.

1562
01:38:11,253 --> 01:38:12,813
You come to see the general a lot?

1563
01:38:12,813 --> 01:38:14,513
Often.

1564
01:38:14,513 --> 01:38:16,463
- She likes a general style.
- I'm a fan.

1565
01:38:16,463 --> 01:38:18,723
I want to see him every day.

1566
01:38:19,773 --> 01:38:21,753
Also, this is the Sejong Center
for the Performing Arts.

1567
01:38:21,753 --> 01:38:24,833
I like this neighborhood even more for that.

1568
01:38:26,613 --> 01:38:29,673
I didn't talk about King Sejong.

1569
01:38:29,673 --> 01:38:32,293
I'm his fan, too.

1570
01:38:32,293 --> 01:38:34,663
- So cute.
- So cute!

1571
01:38:42,173 --> 01:38:43,933
[Closing eyes]

1572
01:38:51,873 --> 01:38:54,423
[Earlier]

1573
01:38:54,423 --> 01:38:55,923
You okay?

1574
01:38:55,923 --> 01:38:58,383
I'm so tired.

1575
01:38:58,383 --> 01:39:00,063
I might go get an IV drip.

1576
01:39:00,063 --> 01:39:01,803
- She's not feeling well.
- Have you gotten that before?

1577
01:39:01,803 --> 01:39:03,153
- A few times.
- It's stress.

1578
01:39:03,153 --> 01:39:07,063
But it's not like I'm sick.

1579
01:39:07,063 --> 01:39:08,583
So it's the same.

1580
01:39:12,643 --> 01:39:14,533
[Yu Gyeong has fallen asleep]

1581
01:39:14,533 --> 01:39:16,273
Aigoo...

1582
01:39:18,143 --> 01:39:20,743
She must feel comfortable around Jun Hyeon.

1583
01:39:31,093 --> 01:39:33,643
[The car enters a building]

1584
01:39:40,923 --> 01:39:42,543
We're here.

1585
01:39:46,493 --> 01:39:48,303
Are you okay?

1586
01:39:56,083 --> 01:39:58,603
Where are we?

1587
01:39:58,603 --> 01:39:59,693
[A hospital in Seoul]

1588
01:39:59,693 --> 01:40:01,693
Maybe this will be good.

1589
01:40:01,693 --> 01:40:04,073
- Really?
- He likes her.

1590
01:40:04,073 --> 01:40:06,093
[Jun Hyeon brings Yu Gyeong to the hospital]

1591
01:40:06,093 --> 01:40:07,383
That's good.

1592
01:40:07,383 --> 01:40:10,303
- He's so dependable.
- Do we need a temperature check?

1593
01:40:10,303 --> 01:40:12,113
Kang Yu Gyeong.

1594
01:40:14,453 --> 01:40:16,533
Yes.

1595
01:40:17,963 --> 01:40:19,603
Yes.

1596
01:40:19,603 --> 01:40:23,643
[He even pays the bill]

1597
01:40:23,643 --> 01:40:29,213
[Waits for Yu Gyeong again]

1598
01:40:33,113 --> 01:40:35,643
How was it?

1599
01:40:35,643 --> 01:40:37,203
Do you feel better?

1600
01:40:37,203 --> 01:40:39,463
Yes. I feel better.

1601
01:40:41,023 --> 01:40:43,073
[Half asleep]

1602
01:40:43,683 --> 01:40:45,743
Were you asleep when it went in?

1603
01:40:45,743 --> 01:40:47,633
A little?

1604
01:40:48,283 --> 01:40:50,153
I think I feel better.

1605
01:40:50,153 --> 01:40:53,033
- Really.
- Thank goodness.

1606
01:40:53,033 --> 01:40:55,473
We can play yut* tomorrow.
(Korean folk game)

1607
01:40:55,473 --> 01:40:57,833
I'm going to win everything tomorrow.

1608
01:40:57,833 --> 01:41:00,683
I don't know the rules, but I'll win.

1609
01:41:04,573 --> 01:41:07,823
- I'm totally back to life.
- Really?

1610
01:41:07,823 --> 01:41:10,743
- Thank you so much.
- What a relief.

1611
01:41:10,743 --> 01:41:14,823
- You're not actually sick, right?
- No.

1612
01:41:14,823 --> 01:41:21,083
After I got back to the house yesterday...

1613
01:41:21,083 --> 01:41:24,663
I kept closing my eyes in the living room.

1614
01:41:24,663 --> 01:41:27,973
- Yesterday?
- I was passed out.

1615
01:41:31,093 --> 01:41:34,303
Sometimes you just want to be still.

1616
01:41:34,303 --> 01:41:36,703
- Be still.
- In silence.

1617
01:41:37,593 --> 01:41:40,553
I really like that.

1618
01:41:40,553 --> 01:41:44,343
When you're with me, you can be silent.

1619
01:41:44,343 --> 01:41:46,493
- Really?
- Really.

1620
01:41:47,893 --> 01:41:49,483
I like it.

1621
01:41:50,613 --> 01:41:55,703
[Silence for Yu Gyeong]

1622
01:42:01,473 --> 01:42:02,613
That's so cool.

1623
01:42:02,613 --> 01:42:05,183
That was his own way
of confessing his feelings.

1624
01:42:05,183 --> 01:42:06,143
Yes, yes.

1625
01:42:06,143 --> 01:42:09,883
I'm the most curious about you,
and I like talking to you the best.

1626
01:42:09,883 --> 01:42:12,723
I have fun spending time
with you, and that's enough.

1627
01:42:12,723 --> 01:42:15,283
[Butterflies to the max]

1628
01:42:15,283 --> 01:42:17,343
He kept firing off those one-liners.

1629
01:42:17,343 --> 01:42:18,663
It's Jun Hyeon-style flirting.

1630
01:42:18,663 --> 01:42:20,863
She told him he was brave for that.

1631
01:42:20,863 --> 01:42:22,883
"I think you're so brave."

1632
01:42:22,883 --> 01:42:25,053
They went deeper than their last date.

1633
01:42:25,053 --> 01:42:26,673
The way Yu Gyeong looks at him...

1634
01:42:26,673 --> 01:42:28,323
She knows he likes her,

1635
01:42:28,323 --> 01:42:32,103
and I think she took him in a little deeper.

1636
01:42:32,103 --> 01:42:35,923
Do you think today changed
Yu Gyeong's mind at all?

1637
01:42:35,923 --> 01:42:38,853
- I think she knows he's a good guy.
- Of course.

1638
01:42:38,853 --> 01:42:41,553
I think she would feel thankful.

1639
01:42:41,553 --> 01:42:47,033
She knows a guy like that exists.

1640
01:42:51,263 --> 01:42:53,183
[Signal House]

1641
01:42:53,183 --> 01:42:55,063
Are we taking the car?

1642
01:42:55,063 --> 01:43:00,383
[Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri leave together]

1643
01:43:07,813 --> 01:43:10,793
[Before asking her out yesterday]

1644
01:43:11,753 --> 01:43:13,903
Hyung...

1645
01:43:14,973 --> 01:43:16,923
This is too hard.

1646
01:43:19,233 --> 01:43:22,323
- He's trying to end it, right?
- He should.

1647
01:43:22,323 --> 01:43:25,163
[Wu Yeol comes downstairs
after much contemplating]

1648
01:43:26,503 --> 01:43:29,773
It is a little late...

1649
01:43:29,773 --> 01:43:32,293
But we still need to talk.

1650
01:43:32,293 --> 01:43:34,603
- He asked her out so dryly.
- Really?

1651
01:43:34,603 --> 01:43:37,173
Sure. Let's do that.

1652
01:43:37,173 --> 01:43:38,733
Do you want to eat something?

1653
01:43:39,953 --> 01:43:41,973
- You're okay?
- He looked around and said no.

1654
01:43:41,973 --> 01:43:44,103
Yu Gyeong is sitting right there.

1655
01:43:44,103 --> 01:43:49,653
[Wu Yeol picked Gyu Ri]

1656
01:43:51,573 --> 01:43:53,093
What?

1657
01:43:54,123 --> 01:43:58,543
Gyu Ri must think today isn't a good time.

1658
01:43:59,433 --> 01:44:04,783
[What is Wu Yeol trying to say?]

1659
01:44:05,933 --> 01:44:08,603
Can you do it?

1660
01:44:10,393 --> 01:44:12,083
It's okay.

1661
01:44:12,083 --> 01:44:13,873
I'm okay.

1662
01:44:15,493 --> 01:44:17,763
Wow, it takes three and a half hours.

1663
01:44:17,763 --> 01:44:19,673
Two and a half, at least.

1664
01:44:34,593 --> 01:44:40,913
When we get there, the sun
will set around 5:30 p.m.

1665
01:44:40,913 --> 01:44:45,493
But we might be able to sit there
for an hour.

1666
01:44:45,493 --> 01:44:47,133
I see.

1667
01:44:48,753 --> 01:44:52,113
Sweet corn.

1668
01:44:53,473 --> 01:44:57,783
I'm going to look up if there are
sweet corn lattes on the way.

1669
01:44:58,923 --> 01:45:00,633
Sounds good.

1670
01:45:02,473 --> 01:45:05,923
I think Gyu Ri feels
that things have changed.

1671
01:45:05,923 --> 01:45:11,923
I'm looking up places to eat...

1672
01:45:17,043 --> 01:45:20,953
I want to talk, but I need to look this up.

1673
01:45:25,773 --> 01:45:27,233
It's quiet.

1674
01:45:35,853 --> 01:45:40,723
So were you talking all day yesterday?

1675
01:45:40,723 --> 01:45:44,733
Pretty much. We ate...

1676
01:45:44,733 --> 01:45:48,723
- We had a glass of whiskey...
- She did? Yu Gyeong?

1677
01:45:48,723 --> 01:45:50,153
A cocktail.

1678
01:45:50,153 --> 01:45:51,243
Sure.

1679
01:45:51,243 --> 01:45:52,743
I had the whiskey.

1680
01:45:59,093 --> 01:46:02,493
Do you think you talk about
different things with each person?

1681
01:46:02,493 --> 01:46:03,543
- Me?
- Yes.

1682
01:46:03,543 --> 01:46:04,703
I think it's all different.

1683
01:46:04,703 --> 01:46:06,733
Really?

1684
01:46:06,733 --> 01:46:07,773
I see.

1685
01:46:07,773 --> 01:46:09,073
I act different, too.

1686
01:46:09,073 --> 01:46:11,173
Wu Yeol is very firm right now.

1687
01:46:11,173 --> 01:46:12,813
I get silly.

1688
01:46:13,603 --> 01:46:15,873
I was trying to express myself, but...

1689
01:46:15,873 --> 01:46:19,493
I don't know how the other person feels.

1690
01:46:19,493 --> 01:46:21,083
I'm so curious.

1691
01:46:25,143 --> 01:46:29,903
I think you can sort of

1692
01:46:31,473 --> 01:46:34,003
see how everyone is feeling, no?

1693
01:46:34,003 --> 01:46:35,913
He's bringing it up first.

1694
01:46:37,373 --> 01:46:41,033
Weren't you ever worried
that looking way too close

1695
01:46:41,033 --> 01:46:44,413
to just one person might push others away?

1696
01:46:44,413 --> 01:46:48,243
Didn't you think it might stop someone
else from approaching you?

1697
01:46:48,243 --> 01:46:50,503
But both of us were being brave.

1698
01:46:51,253 --> 01:46:53,563
And our decisions were correct.

1699
01:46:59,263 --> 01:47:00,933
[Snow on trees]

1700
01:47:00,933 --> 01:47:02,963
What? Is it snowing?

1701
01:47:03,633 --> 01:47:05,363
I think so. It's snowing.

1702
01:47:06,183 --> 01:47:09,103
[Snow is piling up in Gwangwon-do]

1703
01:47:10,713 --> 01:47:14,543
We talked about the East Sea the first week,
and we're here in the last week.

1704
01:47:14,543 --> 01:47:16,603
That's right.

1705
01:47:16,603 --> 01:47:19,223
I think we did everything
we wanted to, though.

1706
01:47:19,223 --> 01:47:21,223
Everything we talked about.

1707
01:47:23,233 --> 01:47:24,553
There's one thing we didn't do.

1708
01:47:24,553 --> 01:47:28,483
You said there's a place you like...

1709
01:47:28,483 --> 01:47:31,423
The izakaya?

1710
01:47:38,693 --> 01:47:41,283
- It's the winter ocean feel.
- I know.

1711
01:47:42,123 --> 01:47:44,353
I was going to say that.

1712
01:47:44,353 --> 01:47:47,563
[They arrive at the beach]

1713
01:48:00,693 --> 01:48:02,243
I love this!

1714
01:48:07,253 --> 01:48:08,753
I love this.

1715
01:48:14,373 --> 01:48:16,743
It feels cathartic.

1716
01:48:16,743 --> 01:48:18,463
Cathartic?

1717
01:48:18,463 --> 01:48:20,133
Why? Are you frustrated?

1718
01:48:20,133 --> 01:48:21,493
Yes.

1719
01:48:23,743 --> 01:48:25,883
Don't go!

1720
01:48:25,883 --> 01:48:28,423
- "Don't go"?
- Who is she talking to?

1721
01:48:29,813 --> 01:48:31,483
- What?
- Is she crying?

1722
01:48:36,833 --> 01:48:38,913
- Oh, no!
- For real?

1723
01:48:38,913 --> 01:48:45,143
[Gyu Ri breaks down in tears]

1724
01:48:51,323 --> 01:48:53,463
She liked Wu Yeol.

1725
01:48:55,943 --> 01:48:58,213
I can stop immediately.

1726
01:49:05,573 --> 01:49:06,823
What happened?

1727
01:49:06,823 --> 01:49:08,253
I don't know.

1728
01:49:16,233 --> 01:49:22,713
I felt our relationship was
heading toward its end.

1729
01:49:22,713 --> 01:49:25,013
So...

1730
01:49:25,013 --> 01:49:28,163
that was a lot to deal with.

1731
01:49:28,163 --> 01:49:30,233
She felt it.

1732
01:49:30,233 --> 01:49:32,913
I choked up because of that.

1733
01:49:43,853 --> 01:49:48,263
It must be good for closure.

1734
01:49:48,263 --> 01:49:50,113
- Emotional closure?
- Yes.

1735
01:49:50,113 --> 01:49:53,023
Yesterday...

1736
01:49:55,183 --> 01:50:01,093
I felt I had to be honest about my feelings.

1737
01:50:02,293 --> 01:50:04,413
So I...

1738
01:50:04,413 --> 01:50:06,713
You're right. I tried to get closure.

1739
01:50:08,903 --> 01:50:11,083
I didn't want to lie.

1740
01:50:15,223 --> 01:50:17,403
I wish I did it sooner.

1741
01:50:17,403 --> 01:50:18,973
He has his hands behind his back.

1742
01:50:18,973 --> 01:50:21,783
- I know.
- That means something.

1743
01:50:24,613 --> 01:50:28,873
[Night has arrived]

1744
01:50:31,443 --> 01:50:33,093
Cheers.

1745
01:50:45,843 --> 01:50:47,493
We did everything.

1746
01:50:47,493 --> 01:50:48,533
We came to the beach...

1747
01:50:48,533 --> 01:50:50,493
- They went out three times.
- Done.

1748
01:50:51,763 --> 01:50:53,113
Is there anything else you want to do?

1749
01:50:53,113 --> 01:50:54,803
- Me?
- Yeah.

1750
01:50:58,113 --> 01:51:00,853
Should we make up something last minute?

1751
01:51:09,143 --> 01:51:10,643
I did everything I wanted to do.

1752
01:51:10,643 --> 01:51:12,503
Really?

1753
01:51:16,483 --> 01:51:18,283
No regrets with my choice.

1754
01:51:19,783 --> 01:51:21,863
I think I did my best.

1755
01:51:26,873 --> 01:51:30,763
Also, honestly...

1756
01:51:30,763 --> 01:51:33,553
I felt like there was
an invisible wall around you.

1757
01:51:34,493 --> 01:51:37,063
Do you think it's just our relationship?

1758
01:51:37,063 --> 01:51:38,893
Or...

1759
01:51:40,203 --> 01:51:43,803
do you think I'm like that with others, too?

1760
01:51:43,803 --> 01:51:48,173
I think there's a wall between
you and the people here.

1761
01:51:48,173 --> 01:51:49,943
Really?

1762
01:51:49,943 --> 01:51:53,253
I told you I see things like that
at the beginning.

1763
01:51:53,253 --> 01:51:54,883
That's what I thought.

1764
01:51:54,883 --> 01:51:57,503
Maybe...

1765
01:52:01,663 --> 01:52:04,403
you didn't really show us

1766
01:52:06,383 --> 01:52:08,623
everything about you?

1767
01:52:09,373 --> 01:52:12,093
That's what I thought.

1768
01:52:13,023 --> 01:52:15,783
If we hadn't come to Gangneung today,

1769
01:52:15,783 --> 01:52:18,673
could we have talked so earnestly?

1770
01:52:19,373 --> 01:52:22,983
Honestly, I thought we needed to talk.

1771
01:52:29,693 --> 01:52:32,913
You told me to do my best.

1772
01:52:33,843 --> 01:52:36,443
So, here...

1773
01:52:37,643 --> 01:52:40,563
I decided to do my best.

1774
01:52:43,433 --> 01:52:45,853
So, I'm going to follow my heart.

1775
01:52:49,283 --> 01:52:51,193
- Let's go.
- Okay.

1776
01:52:51,963 --> 01:52:53,353
Let's go.

1777
01:52:55,023 --> 01:52:59,323
I guess you can be clear but not hurtful.

1778
01:53:01,253 --> 01:53:01,943
Daebak.

1779
01:53:01,943 --> 01:53:04,373
So, super, super, super hypothetically...

1780
01:53:04,373 --> 01:53:05,763
Yeah.

1781
01:53:06,833 --> 01:53:12,433
How would you feel
if I sent you a text today?

1782
01:53:14,493 --> 01:53:16,483
Well...

1783
01:53:16,483 --> 01:53:18,593
Why? Who do you think I'll pick today?

1784
01:53:18,593 --> 01:53:20,283
It's not about today.

1785
01:53:20,283 --> 01:53:21,693
Today isn't important.

1786
01:53:21,693 --> 01:53:23,723
Today is just a day.

1787
01:53:23,723 --> 01:53:25,353
Today's message?

1788
01:53:25,353 --> 01:53:28,573
What's the point this late in the game?

1789
01:53:28,573 --> 01:53:31,713
Wu Yeol doesn't care about today's messages.

1790
01:53:31,713 --> 01:53:33,803
I'm not stupid.

1791
01:53:33,803 --> 01:53:35,123
Right, you're smart.

1792
01:53:35,123 --> 01:53:37,653
I'm not stupid, so...

1793
01:53:38,523 --> 01:53:42,843
You can't just say that. You know this.

1794
01:53:42,843 --> 01:53:45,333
What do you mean? No.

1795
01:53:45,333 --> 01:53:47,243
Seriously...

1796
01:53:47,243 --> 01:53:49,653
No.

1797
01:53:49,653 --> 01:53:53,913
Honestly, we don't have that much time left.

1798
01:53:53,913 --> 01:53:55,213
Right.

1799
01:53:56,083 --> 01:53:58,493
I think I've made up my mind.

1800
01:54:01,003 --> 01:54:07,203
You know that's going to hurt my feelings.
Why do you say that?

1801
01:54:07,203 --> 01:54:08,583
It's just frustrating.

1802
01:54:08,583 --> 01:54:14,683
You saying, "What if I text you?"
all the way until the end.

1803
01:54:16,683 --> 01:54:19,823
- That's...
- But maybe that's my sincere feelings.

1804
01:54:19,823 --> 01:54:21,613
But still...

1805
01:54:21,613 --> 01:54:23,163
What's wrong with that?

1806
01:54:25,323 --> 01:54:26,893
When I...

1807
01:54:28,733 --> 01:54:32,343
When I watched you from afar,

1808
01:54:34,493 --> 01:54:38,913
it felt like you were slipping away.

1809
01:54:38,913 --> 01:54:40,123
Like you were avoiding me.

1810
01:54:40,123 --> 01:54:43,103
As if to say, "Yeah, that's right."

1811
01:54:44,003 --> 01:54:47,433
I didn't say anything, but there were
a few moments I was puzzled.

1812
01:54:47,433 --> 01:54:53,333
But if I were to think of those moments
in the context of myself

1813
01:54:53,333 --> 01:54:57,233
outside of the show,
it'd be clean and simple.

1814
01:54:57,233 --> 01:55:00,333
- That's right.
- My feelings. Whether I liked you or not.

1815
01:55:00,333 --> 01:55:02,913
I could've wrapped things up. I'd be sure.

1816
01:55:02,913 --> 01:55:04,653
But it's different here.

1817
01:55:05,343 --> 01:55:06,553
Wu Yeol...

1818
01:55:06,553 --> 01:55:10,043
As you know, the way I am outside of the show

1819
01:55:10,043 --> 01:55:12,733
is that I don't even go for her
if she acted like this.

1820
01:55:12,733 --> 01:55:17,133
I'd think, "Go ahead.
So, you're like that. I'm like this."

1821
01:55:17,133 --> 01:55:18,893
I would've let her go.

1822
01:55:18,893 --> 01:55:20,623
But it's different in here.

1823
01:55:20,623 --> 01:55:22,253
No...

1824
01:55:22,253 --> 01:55:25,113
- It's not like that.
- That's how I felt.

1825
01:55:25,113 --> 01:55:29,923
Maybe I expected some honesty.
That's why I felt that way.

1826
01:55:31,333 --> 01:55:38,033
I thought that I was more honest than you.

1827
01:55:38,033 --> 01:55:39,663
You're right.

1828
01:55:39,663 --> 01:55:42,633
You must know I have some feelings right now.

1829
01:55:42,633 --> 01:55:46,203
I tried to be...

1830
01:55:47,233 --> 01:55:50,133
honest about my feelings.

1831
01:55:50,133 --> 01:55:57,233
I realized that I must like Yu Gyeong a lot.

1832
01:55:59,223 --> 01:56:03,263
[His true self when he's with Yu Gyeong]

1833
01:56:09,263 --> 01:56:14,143
It's so comfortable with her, and I loved it.

1834
01:56:15,023 --> 01:56:18,713
I strongly sensed that
what I thought was correct.

1835
01:56:18,713 --> 01:56:22,043
I've never seen
anyone spell it out so clearly.

1836
01:56:22,043 --> 01:56:23,603
So...

1837
01:56:25,233 --> 01:56:29,623
my feelings had already been sorted out
before I came out today.

1838
01:56:29,623 --> 01:56:31,733
Does Yu Gyeong know
that he's saying all this?

1839
01:56:31,733 --> 01:56:34,913
This is Signal House after all, but...

1840
01:56:34,913 --> 01:56:42,733
I think I struggled to see you
go for her so outright.

1841
01:56:42,733 --> 01:56:47,803
That's why I felt it was so hard
for me to move forward.

1842
01:56:50,893 --> 01:56:53,403
I understand a bit now.

1843
01:56:55,353 --> 01:56:57,393
I should've told you all this to begin with.

1844
01:56:57,393 --> 01:56:59,753
Instead of beating around the bush.

1845
01:57:00,453 --> 01:57:03,073
That's hurtful, too.

1846
01:57:04,563 --> 01:57:05,563
Really.

1847
01:57:05,563 --> 01:57:08,253
It's daebak. That was so clear.

1848
01:57:09,923 --> 01:57:12,453
No matter who you choose,

1849
01:57:13,363 --> 01:57:15,173
I'll root for you.

1850
01:57:20,343 --> 01:57:22,873
Doesn't this season feel like a drama?

1851
01:57:22,873 --> 01:57:25,633
I'm so dizzy right now.

1852
01:57:25,633 --> 01:57:30,233
- I did actually worry a little bit.
- Sure.

1853
01:57:30,233 --> 01:57:31,733
Yu Gyeong gave him one last chance.

1854
01:57:31,733 --> 01:57:36,693
She forgave him one last time.
And if wavers with Gyu Ri...

1855
01:57:36,693 --> 01:57:39,923
- Yet he's so firm.
- That was so firm.

1856
01:57:39,923 --> 01:57:42,753
He was so firm while the woman
was crying next to him.

1857
01:57:42,753 --> 01:57:44,773
- "You should not cry."
- Really.

1858
01:57:44,773 --> 01:57:48,243
He had his hands behind his back,
like a drill sergeant.

1859
01:57:48,243 --> 01:57:52,293
He told her why he doesn't like her,
and why his feelings are gone.

1860
01:57:52,293 --> 01:57:54,903
And he told her what Yu Gyeong means to him.

1861
01:57:54,903 --> 01:57:57,953
He said, "I think I like Yu Gyeong a lot."

1862
01:57:57,953 --> 01:58:01,063
He was being a straight shooter.

1863
01:58:01,063 --> 01:58:02,723
He wasn't indecisive.

1864
01:58:02,723 --> 01:58:05,513
He said he behaved that way toward
her since it was Heart Signal.

1865
01:58:05,513 --> 01:58:08,283
Right. He wouldn't have behaved
that way outside the show.

1866
01:58:08,283 --> 01:58:10,153
He was so clear.

1867
01:58:10,153 --> 01:58:13,123
And before he said that,
she cried, saying, "Don't go."

1868
01:58:13,123 --> 01:58:16,013
She sensed that he'd leave her.
So she cried, saying, "Don't go."

1869
01:58:16,013 --> 01:58:17,553
She did as soon as they got there.

1870
01:58:17,553 --> 01:58:21,493
But actually, she cried
because she expected it.

1871
01:58:21,493 --> 01:58:23,753
And she wanted to change his mind.

1872
01:58:23,753 --> 01:58:26,003
That's right. She threw it
out there one last time.

1873
01:58:26,003 --> 01:58:28,513
You know how we said,
"Why are they going to Gangneung?"

1874
01:58:28,513 --> 01:58:30,483
"Since I said something to you before,

1875
01:58:30,483 --> 01:58:32,123
I'll keep my word about that.

1876
01:58:32,123 --> 01:58:33,683
But I'll say what I have to say."

1877
01:58:33,683 --> 01:58:37,933
He prepared to say that when he went.
He's quite something.

1878
01:58:37,933 --> 01:58:39,503
- He's something.
- Totally.

1879
01:58:39,503 --> 01:58:42,243
On their way there, he gave away the spoiler.

1880
01:58:42,243 --> 01:58:45,463
He said, "Don't you think
we all know how we feel?"

1881
01:58:45,463 --> 01:58:47,163
He was very firm.

1882
01:58:47,163 --> 01:58:50,493
Wu Yeol is moving our hearts in the end.

1883
01:58:50,493 --> 01:58:54,083
[The tenants have come home after their date]

1884
01:58:55,433 --> 01:58:57,013
I don't think I have anyone but you.

1885
01:58:57,013 --> 01:59:00,173
[Dizzy]

1886
01:59:01,953 --> 01:59:03,483
What?

1887
01:59:03,483 --> 01:59:05,653
Stop doing that.

1888
01:59:09,293 --> 01:59:11,933
I've never seen such a drastic
change after three weeks.

1889
01:59:11,933 --> 01:59:13,733
I know.

1890
01:59:17,663 --> 01:59:20,793
What's wrong? Why are you so down?

1891
01:59:22,073 --> 01:59:24,443
Gosh, I'm regretting something.

1892
01:59:24,443 --> 01:59:26,463
What are you regretting?

1893
01:59:26,463 --> 01:59:29,683
I feel like I put too much pressure on him.

1894
01:59:29,683 --> 01:59:31,283
To Seo Won?

1895
01:59:31,283 --> 01:59:37,333
What pressure? Confessing your feelings
in this place is no pressure.

1896
01:59:37,333 --> 01:59:41,543
If you say that, I'm the one
who pressured Seong Min the most.

1897
01:59:41,543 --> 01:59:46,473
Whether that person
thinks it's pressure or not,

1898
01:59:47,043 --> 01:59:50,033
I think it's up to that person to decide.

1899
01:59:50,033 --> 01:59:52,183
It's something Seo Won should decide.

1900
01:59:52,183 --> 01:59:53,863
Gosh, such nice ladies.

1901
01:59:53,863 --> 01:59:56,863
The reason I feel like I'm pressuring him is

1902
01:59:56,863 --> 01:59:59,863
because I can see how firm Seo Won feels.

1903
01:59:59,863 --> 02:00:04,163
I feel like I've complicated things for him.

1904
02:00:04,163 --> 02:00:06,433
I think I've made things harder for him.

1905
02:00:06,433 --> 02:00:08,713
But you joined us late.

1906
02:00:08,713 --> 02:00:10,153
- You can't help it.
- That's right.

1907
02:00:10,153 --> 02:00:11,753
You came in later than others.

1908
02:00:11,753 --> 02:00:15,483
So, I think it's okay for you to express
your feelings a little late.

1909
02:00:15,483 --> 02:00:16,333
She's right.

1910
02:00:16,333 --> 02:00:19,353
[Tenants have a lot on their mind]

1911
02:00:22,153 --> 02:00:24,273
The strong lady is telling you.

1912
02:00:24,273 --> 02:00:26,913
- Min Ju is pretty much...
- Min Ju is hurting more, So Yun.

1913
02:00:26,913 --> 02:00:29,273
Min Ju is basically
a Buddha statue like that.

1914
02:00:29,273 --> 02:00:31,713
You're so right.

1915
02:00:35,523 --> 02:00:36,433
Are they back?

1916
02:00:36,433 --> 02:00:38,293
[Jun Hyeon and Yu Gyeong arrive home]

1917
02:00:38,293 --> 02:00:40,263
Yu Gyeong and Jun Hyeon.

1918
02:00:41,073 --> 02:00:42,653
Are they upstairs?

1919
02:00:42,653 --> 02:00:45,563
- Everyone...
- Where is everyone?

1920
02:00:45,563 --> 02:00:49,113
[Seo Won was lying down]

1921
02:00:49,113 --> 02:00:50,493
Come.

1922
02:00:51,193 --> 02:00:52,573
Come here.

1923
02:00:52,573 --> 02:00:55,473
- Lie down next to me.
- Get up.

1924
02:00:56,953 --> 02:00:58,813
Get up, Seo Won.

1925
02:00:58,813 --> 02:01:01,353
Seo Won has a headache.

1926
02:01:01,353 --> 02:01:03,203
Did you have fun?

1927
02:01:03,203 --> 02:01:04,953
Yeah.

1928
02:01:04,953 --> 02:01:06,853
What's the score today?

1929
02:01:06,853 --> 02:01:08,203
It was 8 points yesterday.

1930
02:01:08,203 --> 02:01:11,943
[Yu Gyeong spent the day with him today]

1931
02:01:13,153 --> 02:01:14,883
Fifteen points.

1932
02:01:15,683 --> 02:01:17,453
It was fun.

1933
02:01:17,453 --> 02:01:19,333
Nice.

1934
02:01:19,333 --> 02:01:21,283
[He had such a nice date]

1935
02:01:21,283 --> 02:01:24,493
My head hurts because...

1936
02:01:24,493 --> 02:01:27,753
I expected our date to be good, and it was.

1937
02:01:29,373 --> 02:01:32,223
Oh, I guess there is that.

1938
02:01:32,223 --> 02:01:34,703
- Because you enjoyed it so much today?
- Seo Won is so transparent.

1939
02:01:34,703 --> 02:01:35,833
I'm so glad.

1940
02:01:35,833 --> 02:01:38,783
I can't breathe when I'm with So Yun.

1941
02:01:38,783 --> 02:01:40,963
- Because she's so funny?
- No.

1942
02:01:40,963 --> 02:01:43,423
I feel like I'm dealing with apnea.

1943
02:01:44,204 --> 02:01:46,033
I get goosebumps all over...

1944
02:01:46,033 --> 02:01:48,563
Wow! He says he gets goosebumps all over.

1945
02:01:48,563 --> 02:01:50,583
It's complicated.

1946
02:01:50,583 --> 02:01:52,583
[They have a lot on their mind tonight]

1947
02:01:52,583 --> 02:01:55,593
How was it with Wu Yeol yesterday?

1948
02:01:55,593 --> 02:01:58,163
Yesterday was...

1949
02:01:58,983 --> 02:02:00,913
Worrying more won't fix it.

1950
02:02:00,913 --> 02:02:02,803
She's telling them everything.

1951
02:02:02,803 --> 02:02:05,633
We just said, "Let's have fun today."
So, we did.

1952
02:02:05,633 --> 02:02:08,003
Good.

1953
02:02:08,003 --> 02:02:10,283
But...

1954
02:02:10,283 --> 02:02:14,123
I went on three dates with him,
including that time.

1955
02:02:14,123 --> 02:02:15,743
And this time was the most fun.

1956
02:02:15,743 --> 02:02:17,963
- Really?
- I think he did, too.

1957
02:02:17,963 --> 02:02:19,783
That's how he seemed.

1958
02:02:20,563 --> 02:02:22,203
What a bastard...

1959
02:02:22,843 --> 02:02:23,923
[Cracking up]

1960
02:02:23,923 --> 02:02:26,753
[Can't help feeling hurt]

1961
02:02:26,753 --> 02:02:28,663
It's so funny.

1962
02:02:28,663 --> 02:02:31,133
Actually, you have so much feelings for him.

1963
02:02:31,133 --> 02:02:34,133
- That's why you were willing to do so.
- You're right.

1964
02:02:35,033 --> 02:02:37,403
Gosh, today...

1965
02:02:38,113 --> 02:02:39,643
Today was...

1966
02:02:40,853 --> 02:02:43,343
I'm so torn.

1967
02:02:43,343 --> 02:02:45,203
Why?

1968
02:02:46,543 --> 02:02:50,323
The more I talk to Jun Hyeon...

1969
02:02:50,323 --> 02:02:53,283
Yes. That's right.

1970
02:02:54,463 --> 02:02:56,433
My feelings are growing.

1971
02:02:57,193 --> 02:03:01,013
- Really? I think that's so obvious.
- He's a great person.

1972
02:03:01,013 --> 02:03:04,983
Because Jun Hyeon isn't always
a nice guy, you know?

1973
02:03:04,983 --> 02:03:07,053
- I know what that is.
- A little bit of a bad boy?

1974
02:03:07,053 --> 02:03:10,093
He's not a bad boy. He's attractive as a man.

1975
02:03:10,093 --> 02:03:12,623
- He's an attractive man.
- That's right!

1976
02:03:12,623 --> 02:03:14,313
He's so masculine.

1977
02:03:14,313 --> 02:03:18,023
I don't know
why he opens the car door for me.

1978
02:03:18,023 --> 02:03:21,283
So, that does help, huh?

1979
02:03:21,283 --> 02:03:23,263
Opening the door for a lady.

1980
02:03:24,505 --> 02:03:27,783
[Jun Hyeon continues
to open the car door for her]

1981
02:03:27,783 --> 02:03:30,483
It's only possible if that's his norm.

1982
02:03:30,483 --> 02:03:32,633
That makes your heart race, you know!
Opening the car door!

1983
02:03:32,633 --> 02:03:34,993
I don't know because
I've never ridden in a car with him.

1984
02:03:34,993 --> 02:03:36,403
You'd better hurry up and do so.

1985
02:03:36,403 --> 02:03:40,803
I feel like I'm being treated so nicely.

1986
02:03:40,803 --> 02:03:43,203
It feels like a woman-and-man vibe.

1987
02:03:43,203 --> 02:03:46,753
- He's sweet, huh?
- Jun Hyeon is a man!

1988
02:03:46,753 --> 02:03:48,453
But he's the real man.

1989
02:03:48,453 --> 02:03:51,063
But if it's someone else,
you could feel cringey.

1990
02:03:51,063 --> 02:03:52,633
But not Jun Hyeon.

1991
02:03:52,633 --> 02:03:54,203
He's simple and straightforward.

1992
02:03:54,203 --> 02:03:58,493
Don't you think Jun Hyeon is
the most considerate one?

1993
02:03:58,493 --> 02:04:00,553
- What's going on?
- He's the most mature one.

1994
02:04:00,553 --> 02:04:02,373
He's the most mature one.

1995
02:04:02,373 --> 02:04:04,133
He is the oldest, but...

1996
02:04:04,133 --> 02:04:07,033
- Rediscovering Jun Hyeon.
- He's so mature.

1997
02:04:07,033 --> 02:04:08,953
You totally got sucked in.

1998
02:04:08,953 --> 02:04:10,393
Got sucked in...

1999
02:04:10,393 --> 02:04:13,243
We went to an LP bar at the end.

2000
02:04:13,243 --> 02:04:14,783
It was nice...

2001
02:04:15,733 --> 02:04:17,753
- See?
- Lucky.

2002
02:04:17,753 --> 02:04:20,033
Wu Yeol ended it with Gyu Ri.

2003
02:04:20,033 --> 02:04:22,243
And now, Yu Gyeong... what's going on?

2004
02:04:22,243 --> 02:04:23,963
- Wu Yeol is coming to her, but...
- Right.

2005
02:04:23,963 --> 02:04:26,363
Yu Gyeong's heart is...

2006
02:04:26,363 --> 02:04:29,173
- That's why this is so...
- It's all about timing.

2007
02:04:29,173 --> 02:04:32,933
Finally, Jun Hyeon's charm is all out.

2008
02:04:32,933 --> 02:04:35,773
So, why aren't those two back yet?

2009
02:04:35,773 --> 02:04:38,033
Why do you care?

2010
02:04:38,033 --> 02:04:42,193
The one who actually cares
never says it out loud.

2011
02:04:42,193 --> 02:04:44,733
They're going all out.

2012
02:04:44,733 --> 02:04:46,923
Yu Gyeong is once again...

2013
02:04:47,853 --> 02:04:50,653
- It's okay, it's okay.
- This is no good.

2014
02:04:50,653 --> 02:04:52,963
They went to Gangneung, right?

2015
02:04:52,963 --> 02:04:54,173
Who?

2016
02:04:54,173 --> 02:04:56,393
- Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri.
- Huh?

2017
02:04:56,393 --> 02:04:57,773
Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri went to Gangneung.

2018
02:04:57,773 --> 02:04:59,313
I didn't hear that.

2019
02:04:59,313 --> 02:05:01,253
They went to Gangneung?

2020
02:05:05,313 --> 02:05:08,213
Wait a minute. They went to Gangneung?

2021
02:05:08,213 --> 02:05:09,783
I could be wrong.

2022
02:05:09,783 --> 02:05:11,863
He got annoyed just now.

2023
02:05:11,863 --> 02:05:13,793
My head is so...

2024
02:05:18,343 --> 02:05:20,573
They must be on their way back, right?

2025
02:05:20,573 --> 02:05:23,913
But why go all the way to Gangneung?

2026
02:05:23,913 --> 02:05:26,373
Yu Gyeong must have a headache, too.

2027
02:05:28,513 --> 02:05:30,003
What are you going to do?

2028
02:05:30,003 --> 02:05:31,443
[Headache]

2029
02:05:32,423 --> 02:05:35,663
[Door is cruelly shut tight]

2030
02:05:35,663 --> 02:05:37,943
- Don't worry.
- Yes, don't.

2031
02:05:37,943 --> 02:05:40,683
If you're meant to be, you'll be together.

2032
02:05:40,683 --> 02:05:43,093
Right. Even a straw shoe has its pair.

2033
02:05:43,093 --> 02:05:45,503
You keep saying that.

2034
02:05:47,233 --> 02:05:49,703
But I think you can lose your other shoe.

2035
02:05:49,703 --> 02:05:51,413
People lose shoes.

2036
02:05:51,413 --> 02:05:53,783
The slippers are in the wrong pairs.

2037
02:05:53,783 --> 02:05:54,803
Gosh...

2038
02:05:54,803 --> 02:05:56,703
So frustrating.

2039
02:05:57,543 --> 02:05:59,423
There will be the other shoe.

2040
02:06:01,143 --> 02:06:03,413
Somewhere out there.

2041
02:06:05,423 --> 02:06:06,933
But you could lose one.

2042
02:06:06,933 --> 02:06:09,133
- No.
- Seriously.

2043
02:06:13,363 --> 02:06:18,893
[The text results will be revealed next week]

2044
02:06:18,893 --> 02:06:20,933
Did you sleep okay?

2045
02:06:20,933 --> 02:06:22,643
I did.

2046
02:06:22,643 --> 02:06:24,633
- Did you eat?
- No, not yet.

2047
02:06:24,633 --> 02:06:26,283
- Are you hungry?
- Yes.

2048
02:06:26,283 --> 02:06:28,023
Should we eat something?

2049
02:06:28,023 --> 02:06:28,983
Yes.

2050
02:06:28,983 --> 02:06:34,163
But before we eat,
we have to eat these probiotics.

2051
02:06:37,303 --> 02:06:41,223
No matter how young you are,
you should take care of your health.

2052
02:06:43,583 --> 02:06:46,313
I should. Thanks.

2053
02:06:46,313 --> 02:06:47,823
[Drop in the mouth]

2054
02:06:55,843 --> 02:06:57,733
I should keep taking it.

2055
02:06:57,733 --> 02:07:00,063
Take one on an empty stomach.

2056
02:07:01,583 --> 02:07:03,893
So, are you at peace?

2057
02:07:03,893 --> 02:07:08,093
The fact that you're saying
you're at peace...

2058
02:07:08,093 --> 02:07:10,653
Honestly, I feel so empty.

2059
02:07:10,653 --> 02:07:12,513
- Let's have a drink.
- Your first choice was Yu Gyeong.

2060
02:07:12,513 --> 02:07:15,143
- Yu Gyeong.
- Yu Gyeong for me, too.

2061
02:07:16,053 --> 02:07:17,773
I'll be selfish.

2062
02:07:17,773 --> 02:07:20,213
I didn't come here to make friends.

2063
02:07:20,213 --> 02:07:22,053
Oppa...

2064
02:07:22,813 --> 02:07:26,023
The fact that I didn't match up
with the person who changed me...

2065
02:07:26,023 --> 02:07:27,903
It means we missed each other.

2066
02:07:27,903 --> 02:07:29,283
That's right.

2067
02:07:29,283 --> 02:07:30,623
I'm anxious.

2068
02:07:31,973 --> 02:07:33,813
I feel so shy.

2069
02:07:33,813 --> 02:07:35,653
It looks good on you.

2070
02:07:35,653 --> 02:07:37,693
Can I expect more?

2071
02:07:37,693 --> 02:07:40,033
Expect more. You can.

2072
02:07:41,013 --> 02:07:42,913
Who am I with when I'm happiest?

2073
02:07:42,913 --> 02:07:44,743
Who I like.

2074
02:07:44,743 --> 02:07:46,513
I think it was Yu Gyeong.

2075
02:07:46,513 --> 02:07:48,973
- Dol-dol-Yu?
- Yes, Dol-dol-Yu.

2076
02:07:50,383 --> 02:07:52,473
I was bored.

2077
02:07:52,473 --> 02:07:55,263
Someone went on a date. So, I got bored.

2078
02:07:55,263 --> 02:07:57,053
Is that so?

2079
02:07:57,773 --> 02:08:01,353
I think I'm more confused the more we talk.

2080
02:08:01,353 --> 02:08:02,913
The postcard was big.

2081
